(318, 14, 'p5', 'What is the money from TV licences used for?', 'radio', 'The money from TV licences is usedto pay for the British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC). This is a public service broadcaster providing television and radio programmes. The BBC is the largest broadcaster in the world. It is the only wholly state-funded media organisation that is independent of government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
