(331, 14, 'p18', 'Who was the first British distance runner to win a gold medal in the Olympic games in the 10,000 metres?', 'radio', 'Mo Farah(1983-) is a British distance runner, born in Somalia. He won gold medals in the 2012 Olympics for the 5,000 and 10,000 metres and is the first Briton to win the Olympic gold medal in the 10,000 metres.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(332, 14, 'p19', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, 31 December is called Hogmanay and 2 January is also a public holiday.For some Scottish people, Hogmanay is a bigger holiday than Christmas.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
