(391, 17, 'p6', 'What architectural style became popular in the 19th century?', 'radio', 'In the 19th century, themedieval ’gothic’ stylebecame popular again. As cities expanded, many great public buildings were built in this style. The Houses of Parliament and St Pancras Station were built at this time, as were the town halls in cities such as Manchester and Sheffield.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
