(534, 23, 'p5', 'Who were the pioneers of the IVF (in-vitro fertilisation) therapy?', 'radio', 'IVF (in-vitro fertilisation) therapy for the treatment of infertility was pioneered in Britain by physiologistSir Robert Edwards(1925-)and gynaecologist Patrick Steptoe(1913-88). The world’s first ‘test-tube baby’ was born in Oldham, Lancashire in 1978.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(535, 23, 'p6', 'In the UK, bank holidays of no religious significance are celebrated at the beginning of May, in late May or early June, and in August:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(536, 23, 'p7', 'What TWO different types of rugby are practised in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'There are two different types of rugby, which have different rules:union and league.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(537, 23, 'p8', 'What do William Blake, John Keats and Lord Byron have in common?', 'radio', 'Poetry was very popular in the 19th century, with poets such as William Blake, John Keats, Lord Byron, Percy Shelley, Alfred Lord Tennyson, and Robert and Elizabeth Browning.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(538, 23, 'p9', 'The Laurence Olivier Awards take place annually at different venues in Liverpool:', 'radio', 'False. The Laurence Olivier Awards take place annually at different venues in London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(539, 23, 'p10', 'An additional rented piece of land where people can grow fruit and vegetables is known as:', 'radio', 'In the UK, some people rent additional land called‘an allotment’, where they grow fruit and vegetables.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(540, 23, 'p11', 'Which TWO pop music groups became popular in the 1960s?', 'checkbox', 'Two well-known pop music groups in the 1960s wereThe Beatles and The Rolling Stones.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(541, 23, 'p12', 'Eid ul Adha is the day when Muslims thank Allah for giving them the strength to complete the fast:', 'radio', 'False. The day when Muslims thank Allah for giving them the strength to complete the fast is called Eid a-Fitr.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(542, 23, 'p13', 'Which of the following poets wrote poems inspired by Scotland and the traditional stories and songs from the area on the borders of Scotland and England?', 'radio', 'Sir Walter Scottwrote poems inspired by Scotland and the traditional stories and songs from the area on the borders of Scotland and England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(543, 23, 'p14', 'Which golf ‘Major’ tournament is held outside the United States?', 'radio', 'The open championshipis the only ‘Major’ tournament held outside the United States.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(544, 23, 'p15', 'Which is the most famous rugby union competition?', 'radio', 'The most famous rugby union competition isthe Six Nations Championshipbetween England, Ireland, Scotland, Wales, France and Italy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(545, 23, 'p16', 'Which of the following is an ancient festival and has roots in the pagan festival to mark the beginning of winter?', 'radio', 'Halloween, 31 October, is and ancient festival and has roots in the pagan festival to mark the beginning of winter.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(546, 23, 'p17', 'When is the anniversary of the Battle of the Boyne celebrated in Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In Northern Ireland, the anniversary of the Battle of the Boyne is celebrated inJulyand is also a public holiday.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(547, 23, 'p18', 'Who is the head of the Church of England?', 'radio', 'The monarchis the head of the Church of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(548, 23, 'p19', 'In the UK, owners are responsible for keeping their dog under control and for cleaning up after the animal in public places:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(549, 23, 'p20', 'Which British writer wrote satirical novels including ‘Brideshead Revisited’?', 'radio', 'Evelyn Waughwrote satirical novels, including Decline and Fall and Scoop. He is perhaps best known for Brideshead Revisited.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(550, 23, 'p21', 'What was the population of the UK in 1851?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 1851 was20 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(551, 23, 'p22', 'Which book written by JRR Tolkien was voted the country’s best-loved novel in 2003?', 'radio', 'In 2003,The Lord of the Ringsby JRR Tolkien was voted the country’s best-loved novel.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(552, 23, 'p23', 'What is the note with the highest value in the UK?', 'radio', 'The note with the highest value in the UK is the£50note.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(553, 24, 'p0', 'What day does Lent start?', 'radio', 'Lent beginson Ash Wednesday.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(554, 24, 'p1', 'How old do you need to be to be able to apply for a free TV licence?', 'radio', 'Peopleover 75can apply for a free TV licence and blind people can get a 50% discount.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(555, 24, 'p2', 'What time do usually pubs open on Sundays in the UK?', 'radio', 'Pubs are usually open during the day from 11.00 am (12 noon on Sundays).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(556, 24, 'p3', 'Which British sportswoman won two gold medals for running in the 2004 Olympic Games?', 'radio', 'Dame Kelly Holmeswon two gold medals for running in the 2004 Olympic Games. She has held a number of British and European records.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(557, 24, 'p4', 'What percentage of the total British population is located in England alone?', 'radio', 'The population is very unequally distributed over the four parts of the UK. England more or less consistently makes up84%of the total population, Wales around 5%, Scotland just over 8%, and Northern Ireland less than 3%.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(558, 24, 'p5', 'What was the population of the UK in 2010?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 2010 wasjust over 62 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(559, 24, 'p6', 'Which flower is associated with England?', 'radio', 'The roseis the flower associated with England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(560, 24, 'p7', 'In which period did British Film studios flourish?', 'radio', 'British film studios flourishedin the 1930s.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(561, 24, 'p8', 'According to the 2011 Census, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Sikh?', 'radio', 'According to the 2011 Census,0.8% of the populationidentified themselves as Sikh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(562, 24, 'p9', 'Which flower is associated with Wales?', 'radio', 'The daffodilis the flower associated with Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(563, 24, 'p10', 'Which of the following is NOT a city of the UK?', 'radio', 'Dublinis not a city of the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(564, 24, 'p11', 'When is Bonfire Night celebrated?', 'radio', 'Bonfire Night is celebrated on the5th of November.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(565, 24, 'p12', 'Which of the following statements regarding television in Northern Ireland is TRUE?', 'radio', 'There are programmes specific to Northern Ireland andsome programmes broadcast in Irish Gaelic.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(566, 24, 'p13', 'In the second half of the 19th century there was an important group of artists who painted detailed pictures on religious or literary themes in bright colours. These were known as:', 'radio', 'The Pre-Raphaeliteswere an important group of artists in the second half of the 19th century. They painted detailed pictures on religious or literary themes in bright colours. The group included Holman Hunt, Dante Gabriel Rossetti and Sir John Millais.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(567, 24, 'p14', 'The Muslim festival known as Eid ul Adha reminds Muslims of their own commitment to God:', 'radio', 'True. Eid ul Adha reminds Muslims of their own commitment to God.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(568, 24, 'p15', 'What was the population of the UK in 1901?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 1901 was40 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(569, 24, 'p16', 'When is Boxing Day celebrated?', 'radio', 'Boxing Day is the day after Christmas Day and is celebratedon the 26th December.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(570, 24, 'p17', 'Which charity works for the preservation of buildings in England?', 'radio', 'In the UK, many parts of the countryside and places of interest are kept open bythe National Trustin England, Wales and Northern Ireland and the National Trust for Scotland. Both are charities that work to preserve important buildings, coastline and countryside in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(571, 24, 'p18', 'Which of the following is a traditional Welsh food?', 'radio', 'Welsh cakesare a traditional Welsh snack made from flour, dried fruits and spices, and served either hot or cold.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(572, 24, 'p19', 'When is the Jewish celebration known as Hanukkah normally celebrated?', 'radio', 'Hannukah is inNovember or Decemberand is celebrated for eight days.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(573, 24, 'p20', 'What musical award is given during the Mercury Music Prize?', 'radio', 'The Mercury Music Prize is awarded each September for thebest album from the UK and Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(574, 24, 'p21', 'Which TWO of the following water sports are popular in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'Sailingcontinues to be popular in the UK, reflecting our maritime heritage.Rowingis also popular, both as a leisure activity and as a competitive sport.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(575, 24, 'p22', 'In the UK, what should dogs wear in public places?', 'radio', 'All dogs in public places must weara collar showing the name and address of the owner.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(576, 24, 'p23', 'According to the Citizenship Survey carried out in the UK in 2009, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Muslim?', 'radio', 'In the 2009 Citizenship Survey, 70% of people identified themselves as Christian. Much smaller proportions identified themselves asMuslim (4%), Hindu (2%), Sikh (1%), Jewish or Buddhist (both less than 0.5%), and 2% of people followed another religion.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(577, 25, 'p0', 'Members of the European Parliament (MEPs) are elected on the basis of:', 'radio', 'Elections to the European Parliament use a system ofproportional representation, where seats are allocated to each party in proportion to the total number of votes it has won.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(578, 25, 'p1', 'The North Atlantic Treaty Organisation is a group of European and North American countries that was created with which TWO purposes:', 'checkbox', 'NATO is a group of European and North American countries that have agreed to help each other if they come under attack. It also aims to maintain peace between all of its members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(579, 25, 'p2', 'The small claims procedure is used in England and Wales for minor disputes for:', 'radio', 'This procedure is used forclaims of less than £10,000 in England and Walesand £3,000 in Scotland and Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(580, 25, 'p3', 'Which of the following is the responsibility of the Chancellor of the Exchequer?', 'radio', 'Chancellor of the Exchequer is responsible for theeconomy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(581, 25, 'p4', 'Which of the following statements is true?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports called Hansard.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(582, 25, 'p5', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries in the House of Commons but not in the House of Lords:', 'radio', 'False. The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries in both the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(583, 25, 'p6', 'Which of the following organisations has no power to make laws but draws up conventions and charters, including the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms?', 'radio', 'The Council of Europeis responsible for the protection and promotion of human rights in those countries. It has no power to make laws but draws up conventions and charters, the most well-known of which is the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms, usually called the European Convention on Human Rights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(584, 25, 'p7', 'Which Court deals with the most serious criminal cases, such as murder, in Scotland?', 'radio', 'The most serious criminal cases in Scotland, such as murder, are heard at aHigh Courtwith a judge and jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(585, 25, 'p8', 'The leader of the opposition leads his or her party in pointing out what they see as the government’s (choose TWO options):', 'checkbox', 'The leader of the opposition leads his or her party in pointing out what they see as the government’sfailures and weaknesses.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(586, 25, 'p9', 'What is the minimum age requirement to drive a mopped in the UK?', 'radio', 'You need to be at least16years old to ride a moped, and there are other age requirements and special tests for driving large vehicles.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(587, 25, 'p10', 'How many countries formed the European Economic Community (EEC) when it was first created in 1957?', 'radio', 'The European Union (EU), originally called the European Economic Community (EEC), was set up bysix western European countries(Belgium, France, Germany, Italy, Luxembourg and the Netherlands) who signed the Treaty of Rome on 25 March 1957.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(588, 25, 'p11', 'What is donated blood used for?', 'radio', 'Donated blood is used by hospitalsto help people with a wide range of injuries and illnesses.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(589, 25, 'p12', 'In which city is the Northern Ireland Assembly building, also known as Stormont, located?', 'radio', 'In Northern Ireland elected members, known as MLAs, meet in the Northern Ireland Assembly at Stormont, inBelfast.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(590, 25, 'p13', 'What can living people donate that may help other people with injuries or illnesses (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'Living people can donateblood and a kidney.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(591, 25, 'p14', 'Where is the office of the MPs located?', 'radio', 'The MP’s office is located atThe House of Commons, Westminster, London, SW1A OAA.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(592, 25, 'p15', 'Which TWO of the following statements is TRUE with regards to Magistrates and Justices of the Peace (JPs) in England, Wales and Scotland?', 'checkbox', 'In England, Wales and Scotland Magistrates and Justices of the Peace (JPs)usually work unpaid and do not need legal qualifications.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(593, 25, 'p16', 'The House of Commons is normally more independent of the government than the House of Lords:', 'radio', 'False. The House of Lords is normally more independent of the government than the House of Commons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(594, 25, 'p17', 'In Northern Ireland members of the Legislative Assembly (MLAs) are elected on the basis of:', 'radio', '﻿The Northern Ireland Assembly has 90 elected members, known as MLAs (members of the Legislative Assembly). They are elected with a form ofproportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(595, 25, 'p18', 'How can MPs be contacted (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'MPs can be contactedby letter or telephone at their constituency office, or at their office in the House of Commons. In addition, many MPs, SMs and MSPs hold regular local ‘surgeries’, where constituents can go in person to talk about issues that are of concern to them.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(596, 25, 'p19', 'Does Britain have a written constitution?', 'radio', 'The British constitution is not written downin any single document, and therefore it is described as ‘unwritten’. This is mainly because the UK, unlike America or France, has never had a revolution which led permanently to a totally new system of government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(597, 25, 'p20', 'When were the United Nations set up?', 'radio', 'The UN was set upafter the Second World Warand aims to prevent war and promote international peace and security.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(598, 25, 'p21', 'Where can you find copies of the ‘Hansard’?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports called Hansard. Written reports can be foundin large libraries and at www.parliament.uk.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(599, 25, 'p22', 'Which court normally deals with cases of children aged 10 to 17 in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in aYouth Courtin front of up to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge. The most serious cases will go the Crown Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(600, 25, 'p23', 'How many senior MPs are appointed by the Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The Prime Minister appointsabout 20 senior MPsto become ministers in charge of departments.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(601, 26, 'p0', 'Where is the official home of the Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The official home of the Prime Minister is10 Downing Street, in central London, near the Houses of Parliament. He or she also has a country house outside London called Chequers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(602, 26, 'p1', 'What name is given to the elected members of the European Parliament?', 'radio', 'Elections for the European Parliament are held every five years. Elected members are called members of the European Parliament (MEPs).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(603, 26, 'p2', 'Which court deals with cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract and divorce in England and Wales?', 'radio', 'County Courtsdeal with a wide range of civil disputes. These include people trying to get back money that is owed to them, cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract, and divorce. In Scotland, most of these matters are dealt with in the Sheriff Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(604, 26, 'p3', 'What is the name of the building where the Scottish Parliament meet?', 'radio', 'In Scotland the elected members, called MSPs, meet in the Scottish Parliament building atHolyroodin Edinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(605, 26, 'p4', 'Which court deals with minor criminal cases in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, most minor criminal cases are dealt with in aMagistrates’ Court. In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to a Justice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(606, 26, 'p5', 'On which issues can the Northern Ireland Assembly NOT make decisions?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly can make decisions on issues such as education, agriculture, the environment, health and social services.It cannot make decisions on defence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `test_id`, `question_id`, `question_text`, `question_type`, `explanation`, `created_at`) VALUES
(607, 26, 'p6', 'What is the first verse of the National Anthem of the UK ‘God save the King’?', 'radio', 'The first verse of the National Anthem of the UK is‘God save our gracious King!.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(608, 26, 'p7', 'Who forms the shadow cabinet?', 'radio', 'The leader of the opposition appoints senior opposition MPsto be ‘shadow ministers’. They form the shadow cabinet and their role is to challenge the government and put forward alternative policies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(609, 26, 'p8', 'People in the UK have to pay tax on any earnings from (choose THREE options)?', 'checkbox', 'People in the UK have to pay tax on their income, which includes: wages from paid employment,profits from self-employment, taxable benefits, pensions and income from property, savings and dividends.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(610, 26, 'p9', 'How many devolved administrations are there in the UK?', 'radio', 'There arethree devolved administrationsin the UK, this include: the Welsh government, the Scottish Parliament and the Northern Ireland Assembly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(611, 26, 'p10', 'Who is responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly?', 'radio', 'Judges (who are together called‘the judiciary’) are responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(612, 26, 'p11', 'How often do people who are 70 years old or over need to renew their driving licence?', 'radio', 'Drivers can use their driving licence until they are 70 years old. After that, the licence isvalid for three yearsat a time.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(613, 26, 'p12', 'Where are the Welsh government and the Senedd based?', 'radio', 'The Welsh government and the Senedd are based inCardiff, the capital city of Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(614, 26, 'p13', 'Which of the following is not a member of the European Union?', 'radio', 'Norwayis not a member of the European Union.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(615, 26, 'p14', 'In the UK, alcohol cannot be sold to anyone under the age of:', 'radio', 'It is a criminal offence to sell alcohol to anyone who is under18or to buy alcohol for people who are under the age of 18. (There is one exception: people aged 16 or over can drink alcohol with a meal in a hotel or restaurant.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(616, 26, 'p15', 'To whom do new citizens have to swear or affirm loyalty as part of the citizenship ceremony?', 'radio', 'New citizens swear or affirm loyalty tothe Kingas part of the citizenship ceremony.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(617, 26, 'p16', 'How can you visit the UK Parliament (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'To visit the UK Parliament,you can write to your local MP in advance to ask for tickets or you can Queue on the day at the public entrance.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(618, 26, 'p17', 'Forced marriage is where one or both parties do not or cannot give their consent to enter into the partnership:', 'radio', 'True. Forced marriage is where one or both parties do not or cannot give their consent to enter into the partnership.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(619, 26, 'p18', 'Which of the following drugs is illegal in the UK?', 'radio', 'Drugs such as heroin, cocaine, ecstasy and cannabis are illegal in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(620, 26, 'p19', 'What is the name of the building where the Northern Ireland Assembly meet?', 'radio', 'In Northern Ireland elected members, known as MLAs, meet in the Northern Ireland Assembly atStormont, in Belfast.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(621, 26, 'p20', 'Which of the following countries is NOT a member of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'Zimbabweis not a member of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(622, 26, 'p21', 'Who makes the decisions on government policies in the UK?', 'radio', 'Decisions on government policies are made bythe Prime Minister and cabinet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(623, 26, 'p22', 'How often is the electoral register updated?', 'radio', 'The electoral register is updatedevery year in September or October.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(624, 26, 'p23', 'What do you need to be able to drive a car in the UK?', 'radio', 'To drive a car in the UK you needa driving licence, a valid motor insurance, a MOT certificate(for cars over three years old)and the road tax.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(625, 27, 'p0', 'How many members does the Scottish Parliament have?', 'radio', 'There are129 membersof the Scottish Parliament (MSPs), elected by a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(626, 27, 'p1', 'What does the term ‘coalition’ refer to?', 'radio', 'The government is usually formed by the party that wins the majority of constituencies.If no party wins a majority, two parties may join together to form a coalition.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(627, 27, 'p2', 'How much do you have to pay to visit the Palace of Westminster?', 'radio', 'The entrance to the Palace of Westminster isfree.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(628, 27, 'p3', 'Civil servants cannot stand for public office:', 'radio', 'True. Most citizens of the UK, the Irish republic or the Commonwealth aged 18 or over can stand for public office. There are some exceptions, including: members of the armed forces, civil servants, people found guilty of certain criminal offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(629, 27, 'p4', 'What is the main function of the Council of Europe?', 'radio', '﻿The Council of Europe has 47 member countries, including the UK, and is responsible forthe protection and promotion of human rightsin those countries.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(630, 27, 'p5', 'In which of the following areas has the Welsh government the power to make laws (choose four)?', 'checkbox', 'The Welsh government has the power to make laws in 20 areas, including:education and training, health and social services, economic development and housing.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(631, 27, 'p6', 'How many members comprise the UN Security Council?', 'radio', 'There are15 memberson the UN Security Council, which recommends action when there are international crises and threats to peace.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(632, 27, 'p7', 'Members in the Senedd can speak English and Welsh, but all publications of the Senedd must be in English:', 'radio', 'False. Members in the Senedd can speak either in English or Welsh, and all of the Senedd\\\'s publications are in both languages.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(633, 27, 'p8', 'How many members does the Northern Ireland Assembly have?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly has90 elected members, known as MLAs (Members of the Legislative Assembly). They are elected with a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(634, 27, 'p9', 'Which of the following civil laws include disputes between landlords and tenants over issues such as repairs and eviction?', 'radio', 'Housing lawincludes disputes between landlords and tenants over issues suck as repairs and eviction.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(635, 27, 'p10', 'How can you visit the Scottish Parliament?', 'radio', 'To visit the Scottish Parliament, you can get information, book tickets orarrange tours through visitor services. You can also write to them at the Scottish Parliament, Edinburgh, EH99 1SP, telephone 0131 348 5200 or email sp.booking@scottish.parliament.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(636, 27, 'p11', 'Which of the following is NOT a duty of the police?', 'radio', 'The job of the police in the UK is to protect life and property, prevent disturbances (also known as keeping the peace) and prevent and detect crime.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(637, 27, 'p12', 'How often are the elections for the European Parliament held?', 'radio', 'Elections for the European Parliament are heldevery five years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(638, 27, 'p13', 'What do new citizens have to swear or affirm as part of the citizenship ceremony?', 'radio', 'New citizens swear or affirmloyalty to the Kingas part of the citizenship ceremony.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(639, 27, 'p14', 'In which TWO cases may a person who has been summoned to do jury service be exempted from doing it:', 'checkbox', 'Everyone who is summoned to do jury service must do it unless they are not eligible: for example, becausethey have a criminal conviction or if they provide a good reason to be excused, such as ill health.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(640, 27, 'p15', 'What is the role of the shadow cabinet?', 'radio', 'The role of the shadow cabinet isto challenge the government and put forward alternative policies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(641, 27, 'p16', 'If you are self-employed:', 'radio', 'If you are self-employed,you need to pay your own taxthrough a system called ‘self-assessment’, which includes completing a tax return.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(642, 27, 'p17', 'What name is given to the elected members of the Northern Ireland Assembly?', 'radio', 'Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly are known asMLAs (members of the Legislative Assembly).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(643, 27, 'p18', 'Which senior MP is responsible for issues relating to crime, policing and immigration?', 'radio', 'The Home Secretaryis responsible for crime, policing and immigration.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(644, 27, 'p19', 'How can a person be protected from being forced into a marriage?', 'radio', 'Court orders can be obtained to protect a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(645, 27, 'p20', 'Which of the following is NOT classified as a criminal offence in the UK?', 'radio', 'Unfair dismissal or discrimination in the workplaceis classified as a civil offence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(646, 27, 'p21', 'Which of the following is NOT considered to be a main part of the British government?', 'radio', 'The European Councilis not part of the British government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(647, 27, 'p22', 'Who appoints the members of the Cabinet?', 'radio', 'The Prime Minister (PM)is the leader of the political party in power. He or she appoints the members of the cabinet and has control over many important public appointments.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(648, 27, 'p23', 'Which court usually deals with the MOST serious civil cases in Scotland?', 'radio', 'More serious civil cases – for example, when a large amount of compensation is being claimed – are dealt with in the High Court of England, Wales and Northern Ireland. In Scotland, they are dealt with inthe Court of Sessionin Edinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(649, 28, 'p0', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'Forcing another person to marry is a criminal offence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(650, 28, 'p1', 'Where do UK residents need to register their car or motorcycle?', 'radio', 'If you are resident in the UK, your car or motor cycle must be registeredat the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(651, 28, 'p2', 'Which court deals with serious criminal offences in Wales?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, serious criminal offences are tried in front of a judge and a jury in aCrown Court. In Scotland, serious cases are heard in a Sheriff Court with either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(652, 28, 'p3', 'When were Protection Orders to protect a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage introduced for Scotland?', 'radio', 'Forced Marriage Protection Orders were introduced in 2008 for England, Wales and Northern Ireland under the Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007. Court orders can be obtained to protect a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage. Similar Protection Orders were introduced in Scotland in November2011.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(653, 28, 'p4', 'Since when have hereditary peers lost the automatic right to attend the House of Lords?', 'radio', '﻿Since 1999, hereditary peers have lost the automatic right to attend the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(654, 28, 'p5', 'What name is given to the elected members of the Welsh government?', 'radio', 'There are 60members of the Senedd (SMs)and elections are held every four years using a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(655, 28, 'p6', 'How often do the ministers that form the Cabinet meet to make important decisions about government policy?', 'radio', 'The cabinet is a committee which usually meetsweeklyand makes important decisions about government policy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(656, 28, 'p7', 'How many countries are members of the United Nations?', 'radio', 'The UK is part of the United Nations (UN), an international organization withmore than 190 countriesas members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(657, 28, 'p8', 'Which of the following statements is true?', 'radio', 'The police force is a public service that helps and protects everyone, no matter what their background or where they live.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(658, 28, 'p9', 'What is the system by which the income tax is automatically taken from the employee’s income by their employer and paid directly to HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC)?', 'radio', 'For most people, the right amount of income tax is automatically taken from their income from employment by their employer and paid directly to HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC), the government department that collects taxes. This system is called“Pay As You Earn” (PAYE).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(659, 28, 'p10', 'How many local authorities are there in London?', 'radio', 'London has33 local authorities, with the Greater London Authority and the Mayor of London coordinating policies across the capital.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(660, 28, 'p11', 'Who is the head of the state in the UK?', 'radio', 'King Charles IIIis the head of state of the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(661, 28, 'p12', 'Members of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs) are elected on the basis of:', 'radio', 'Members of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs) are elected by a form ofproportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(662, 28, 'p13', 'The action of handing out leaflets in the street or knocking on people’s doors to ask for their political support is known as:', 'radio', 'The action of handing out leaflets in the street or knocking on people’s doors to ask for their political support is known ascanvassing.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(663, 28, 'p14', 'Which of the following is a charity that works with old people?', 'radio', 'Age UKis a charity that works with old people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(664, 28, 'p15', 'How many members does the Council of Europe have?', 'radio', 'The Council of Europe is separate from the EU. It has47 member countries, including the UK, and is responsible for the protection and promotion of human rights in those countries.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(665, 28, 'p16', 'In the UK, Members of the Parliament (MPs) are elected on the basis of:', 'radio', 'MPs are elected through a system called‘first past the post’. In  constituency, the candidate who gets the most votes is elected.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(666, 28, 'p17', 'People in the UK do NOT have to pay tax on:', 'radio', 'People in the UK have to pay tax on their income, which includes: wages from paid employment, profits from self-employment, taxable benefits, pensions and income from property, savings and dividends.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(667, 28, 'p18', 'What Treaty established the European Economic Union in 1957?', 'radio', 'The European Union (EU), originally called the European Economic Community (EEC), was set up by six western European countries (Belgium, France, Germany, Italy, Luxembourg and the Netherlands) who signedthe Treaty of Romeon 25 March 1957.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(668, 28, 'p19', 'When did hereditary peers lose the automatic right to attend the House of Lords?', 'radio', 'Since1999, hereditary peers have lost the automatic right to attend the House of Lords. They now elect a few of their number to represent them in the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(669, 28, 'p20', 'When did the King start reining?', 'radio', 'The King has reigned since his mother’s death in September2022.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(670, 28, 'p21', 'Members of the public are not allowed in Youth Courts, and the name or photographs of the accused young person cannot be published in newspapers or used by the media:', 'radio', 'True. Members of the public are not allowed in Youth Courts, and the name or photographs of the accused young person cannot be published in newspapers or used by the media.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(671, 28, 'p22', 'How do we call a set of principles by which a country is governed and which includes all of the institutions that are responsible for running the country and how their power is kept in check?', 'radio', 'Aconstitutionis a set of principles by which a country is governed. It includes all of the institutions that are responsible for running the country and how their power is kept in check.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(672, 28, 'p23', '﻿What is the National Anthem of the UK?', 'radio', 'The National Anthem of the UK is‘God Save the king’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(673, 29, 'p0', 'The Commonwealth has no power over its members and it cannot suspend their membership:', 'radio', 'False. The Commonwealth has no power over its members, although it can suspend membership.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(674, 29, 'p1', 'Which TWO of the following are environmental charities?', 'checkbox', 'The National Trust and Friends of the Earthare environmental charities.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(675, 29, 'p2', 'How often are elections held for the Senedd?', 'radio', 'The Senedd has 60 Senedd members (SMs) and elections are heldevery four yearsusing a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(676, 29, 'p3', 'What is the name given to the person appointed by local authorities to be the ceremonial leader of a particular council?', 'radio', 'Many local authorities appoint amayor, who is the ceremonial leader of the council. In some towns, a mayor is elected to be the effective leader of the administration.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(677, 29, 'p4', 'What is the meaning of the term ‘first past the post’?', 'radio', 'MPs are elected through a system called ‘first past the post’.In each constituency, the candidate who gets the most votes is elected.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(678, 29, 'p5', 'Which court deals with the MOST serious criminal cases in Scotland, such as murder?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, serious cases are heard in a Sheriff Court with either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury. The most serious cases in Scotland, such as murder, are heard at aHigh Courtwith a judge and jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(679, 29, 'p6', 'Who is the ceremonial head of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'The Kingis the ceremonial head of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(680, 29, 'p7', 'Who is the chief officer of the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'The Speakeris the chief officer of the House of Commons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(681, 29, 'p8', 'What characterises the British constitution?', 'radio', 'The British constitution is not written down in any single document, and thereforeit is described as ‘unwritten’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(682, 29, 'p9', 'Who forms the judiciary?', 'radio', 'Judges(who are together called ‘the judiciary’) are responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(683, 29, 'p10', 'Which court deals with minor criminal offences in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to aJustice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(684, 29, 'p11', 'If an MP dies or resigns, there will be a fresh election, which is known as:', 'radio', 'If an MP dies or resigns, there will be a fresh election, called aby-election, in his or her constituency.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(685, 29, 'p12', 'A person who has not paid enough National Insurance contributions will not be able to receive certain contributory benefits including (choose TWO options):', 'checkbox', 'Anyone who does not pay enough National Insurance Contributions will not be able to receive certain contributory benefits such asJobseeker’s Allowance or a full state retirement pension.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(686, 29, 'p13', 'How are life peers appointed?', 'radio', 'Life peers are appointedby the monarch on the advice of the Prime Minister.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(687, 29, 'p14', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 18, the case will be heard in a Youth Court:', 'radio', 'False. In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in a Youth Court in front of up to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(688, 29, 'p15', 'The UN was set up after the First World War and aims to prevent war and promote international peace and security:', 'radio', 'False. The UN was set up after the Second World War and aims to prevent war and promote international peace and security.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(689, 29, 'p16', 'What is played at important national occasions and at events attended by the King or the Royal Family?', 'radio', 'The National Anthemof the UK is ‘God Save the King’ is played at important national occasions and at events attended by the King or the Royal Family.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(690, 29, 'p17', 'How many members does a jury have in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland a jury has 12 members, andin Scotland a jury has 15 members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(691, 29, 'p18', 'How can you visit the Northern Ireland Assembly (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'There are two ways to arrange a visit to the Northern Ireland Assembly at Stormont. You can eithercontact the Education Service(details are on the Northern Ireland Assembly website at http://www.niassembly.gov.uk)or contact an MLA.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(692, 29, 'p19', 'Most citizens of the UK, the Irish republic or the Commonwealth aged 18 or over can stand for public office, except for (choose THREE options):', 'checkbox', 'Members of the Commonwealth aged 18 or over can stand for public office. There are some exceptions, including:members of the armed forces, civil servants and people found guilty of certain criminal offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(693, 29, 'p20', 'On which of the following issues the  Northern Ireland Assembly CANNOT make decisions?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly can make decisions on issues such as education, agriculture, the environment, health and social services.It cannot make decisions on planning issues.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(694, 29, 'p21', 'In which city is the Scottish Parliament building, also known as Holyrood, located?', 'radio', 'In Scotland the elected members, called MSPs, meet in the Scottish Parliament building at Holyrood inEdinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(695, 29, 'p22', 'What name is given to the elected members of the Scottish Parliament?', 'radio', 'Elected members of the Scottish Parliament are known asMembers of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs).', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(696, 29, 'p23', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries located in:', 'radio', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries inboth the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(697, 30, 'p0', 'Which court deals with the most serious cases of children aged 10 to 17 in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in a Youth Court in front of up to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge. The most serious cases will gothe Crown Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(698, 30, 'p1', 'When was the National Trust founded?', 'radio', 'The National Trust was founded in1895by three volunteers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(699, 30, 'p2', 'Who is married to the King of the United Kingdom?', 'radio', 'The King is married toCamilla, the Queen Consort.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(700, 30, 'p3', 'What is the name of the building where the Senedd members meet?', 'radio', 'In Wales the elected members, known as SMs, meet in theSenedd building in Cardiff Bay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(701, 30, 'p4', 'When did the ‘Habeas Corpus Act’ become law?', 'radio', 'The Habeas Corpus Act became law in1679.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(702, 30, 'p5', 'When was the Treaty of Rome signed?', 'radio', 'The European Union (EU), originally called the European Economic Community (EEC), was set up by six western European countries (Belgium, France, Germany, Italy, Luxembourg and the Netherlands) who signed the Treaty of Rome on the25th March 1957.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(703, 30, 'p6', 'The King is the head of state in the UK:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(704, 30, 'p7', 'How often are the general elections held in the UK?', 'radio', 'MPs are elected at a General Election, which is held at leastevery five years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(705, 30, 'p8', 'What is the name of the building where the Northern Ireland Assembly members meet?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly building is known asStormont.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(706, 30, 'p9', 'Which of the following is NOT a function of the House of Lords?', 'radio', 'The House of Lords can suggest amendments or propose new laws, which are then discussed by MPs. The House of Lords checks laws that have been passed by the House of Commons to ensure they are fit for purpose. It also holds the government to account to make sure that it is working in the best interests of the people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(707, 30, 'p10', 'How is the Speaker elected?', 'radio', 'The Speaker is chosenby other MPs in a secret ballot.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(708, 30, 'p11', 'When was the Northern Ireland Parliament established for the first time?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Parliament was first established in1922.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(709, 30, 'p12', 'What name is given to the system used to deal with children and young people who have committed an offence in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In Scotland a system calledthe Children’s Hearings Systemis used to deal with children and young people who have committed an offence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(710, 30, 'p13', 'What is the function of the UN Security Council?', 'radio', 'The UN Security Councilrecommends action when there are international crises and threats to peace.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(711, 30, 'p14', 'Which of the following charities works for the prevention of cruelty to children?', 'radio', 'The NSPCCis the National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(712, 30, 'p15', 'What does the term ‘Hansard’ relate to?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports called Hansard.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(713, 30, 'p16', 'In Wales, the jury has to listen to the evidence presented at the trial and then decide a verdict of ‘guilty’, ‘not guilty’ or ‘not proven’ based of what they have heard:', 'radio', 'False. The jury has to listen to the evidence presented at the trial and then decide a verdict of ‘guilty’ or ‘not guilty’ based of what they have heard. In Scotland (not Wales), a third verdict of ‘not proven’ is also possible.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(714, 30, 'p17', 'A National Insurance number does on its own prove to an employer that you have the right to work in the UK:', 'radio', 'False. A National Insurance number does not on its own prove to an employer that you have the right to work in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(715, 30, 'p18', 'When driving in the UK, where do you need to display the tax disc which shows that the annual road tax has been paid?', 'radio', 'When driving in the UK, you must pay an annual road tax and display the tax disc, which shows that the tax has been paid,on the windowscreen.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(716, 30, 'p19', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'A jury is made up of members of the public chosen at random from the local electoral register.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(717, 30, 'p20', 'It is a civil offence to cause harassment, alarm or distress to someone because of their religion or ethnic origin:', 'radio', 'False. It is a criminal offence to cause harassment, alarm or distress to someone because of their religion or ethnic origin.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(718, 30, 'p21', 'Where can you get contact details for all your representatives and their parties (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'You can get contact details for all your representatives and their parties fromyour local library and from http://www.parliament.uk.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(719, 30, 'p22', 'What is the Old Bailey?', 'radio', 'The Old Bailey is probablythe most famous criminal court in the world.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(720, 30, 'p23', 'What is the relationship between the monarch and the government?', 'radio', 'The monarch has regular meetings with the Prime Minister and can advise, warn and encourage, but the decisions on government policies are made by the Prime Minister and cabinet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(721, 31, 'p0', 'The UK is a ‘constitutional monarchy’:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(722, 31, 'p1', 'Where can people facing domestic violence get help from (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'A solicitor or the Citizens Advice Bureaucan explain the available options to anyone facing domestic violence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(723, 31, 'p2', 'People might be taken to court if they owe money to someone:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(724, 31, 'p3', 'How many members does a jury have in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland a jury has12 members, and in Scotland a jury has 15 members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:43'),
(725, 31, 'p4', 'What TWO tests do you need to pass to get a driving licence in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'To get a UK driving licence you must pass a driving test, which tests both your knowledge and your practical skills.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(726, 31, 'p5', 'What is the role of the Speaker?', 'radio', 'The Speakerkeeps order during political debates to make sure the rules are followed.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(727, 31, 'p6', 'Which of the following statements is FALSE regarding Youth Courts?', 'radio', 'They are usedfor trials of young people aged 10 to 17.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(728, 31, 'p7', 'Who is responsible for the creation of the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms?', 'radio', 'The Council of Europehas no power to make laws but draws up conventions and charters, the most well-known of which is the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(729, 31, 'p8', 'Members of the House of Lords may stand for election to the House of Commons and are eligible for all public offices:', 'radio', 'False. Members of the House of Lords may not stand for election to the House of Commons but are eligible for all other public offices.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(730, 31, 'p9', 'What does the following term ‘PDSA’ stand for?', 'radio', 'PDSA’ stands forPeople’s Dispensary for Sick Animals.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(731, 31, 'p10', 'The Commonwealth is based on the core values of democracy, good government and the rule of law:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(732, 31, 'p11', 'How long does it take to donate blood?', 'radio', 'Giving blood only takesabout an hourto do.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(733, 31, 'p12', 'Where do local authorities get funding from (choose TWO answers)?', 'checkbox', 'Local authorities are funded by money fromthe central government and by local taxes.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(734, 31, 'p13', 'What does the term MEPs stand for?', 'radio', 'MEPs stands forMembers of the European Parliament.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(735, 31, 'p14', 'In which of the following matters can the Scottish Parliament legislate (choose FIVE options)?', 'checkbox', 'The Scottish Parliament can legislate on:civil and criminal law, health, education, planning and additional tax-raising powers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(736, 31, 'p15', 'Drinking in public can be a criminal offence and you can be fined or arrested for it:', 'radio', 'This stamens istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(737, 31, 'p16', 'Whose details are NOT listed in the Phone Book?', 'radio', 'MPs, SMs and MSPs are listed in The Phone Book.The King is not.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(738, 31, 'p17', 'What is the name of the official reports where the Parliament’s proceedings are published?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports calledHansard.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(739, 31, 'p18', 'How many members does the Senedd have?', 'radio', 'The Senedd has60 Senedd members (SMs)and elections are held every four years using a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(740, 31, 'p19', 'Who deals with cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract and divorce in Scotland?', 'radio', 'Civil disputes such as people trying to get back money that is owed to them, cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract, and divorce are dealt with inthe Sheriff Courtin Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(741, 31, 'p20', 'What name is given to the members of the House of Lords?', 'radio', 'Members of the House of Lords are known aspeers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(742, 31, 'p21', 'Magistrates and Justices of the Peace (JPs) are members of:', 'radio', 'Magistrates and Justices of the Peace (JPs) are members ofthe local community.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(743, 31, 'p22', 'How can you visit the Northern Ireland Assembly (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'There are two ways to arrange a visit to the Northern Ireland Assembly at Stormont. You can eithercontact the Education Service(details are on the Northern Ireland Assembly website at http://www.niassembly.gov.uk)or contact an MLA.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(744, 31, 'p23', 'For what sort of claims is the small claims procedure in Northern Ireland used?', 'radio', 'The small claims procedure is used for claims of less than £10,000 in England and Wales andless than £3,000 in Scotland and Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(745, 32, 'p0', 'Which TWO of the following charities work with homeless people?', 'checkbox', '﻿harities working with homeless people includeShelter and Crisis.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(746, 32, 'p1', 'Members of the Senedd (SMs) are elected every four years on the basis of:', 'radio', 'The Senedd has 60 Senedd members (SMs) and elections are held every four years using a form ofproportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(747, 32, 'p2', 'What is the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'The Commonwealth isan association of countries that support each other and work together towards shared goals in democracy and development.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(748, 32, 'p3', 'When was the voting age reduced to 18 for men and women?', 'radio', 'In1969, the voting age was reduced to 18 for men and women.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(749, 32, 'p4', 'When was the Northern Ireland Parliament established for the first time?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Parliament established for the first time in1922.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(750, 32, 'p5', 'What is the opposition?', 'radio', 'The second largest party in the House of Commonsis called the opposition.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(751, 32, 'p6', 'Which THREE of the following groups form part of the British government?', 'checkbox', 'In the UK, there are several different parts of government. The main ones are:the monarchy, the Parliament(the House of Commons and the House of Lords),the Prime Minister, the cabinet, the judiciary (courts), the police, the civil service and the local government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(752, 32, 'p7', 'Who chairs the debates in the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'Debates in the House of Commons are chaired bythe Speaker.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(753, 32, 'p8', 'A woman who is violent towards her partner cannot be prosecuted in the UK:', 'radio', 'False. Anyone who is violent towards their partner – whether they are a man or a woman, married or living together – can be prosecuted.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(754, 32, 'p9', 'Many MPs, SMs and MSPs hold regular local events where constituents can go in person to talk about issues that are of concern to them. These are known as:', 'radio', 'Many MPs, SMs and MSPs hold regularlocal ‘surgeries’, where constituents can go in person to talk about issues that are of concern to them.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(755, 32, 'p10', 'Which Act introduced the Forced Marriage Protection Orders for England, Wales and Northern Ireland in 2008?', 'radio', 'Forced Marriage Protection Orders were introduced in 2008 for England, Wales and Northern Ireland underthe Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007. Similar Protection Orders were introduced in Scotland in November 2011.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(756, 32, 'p11', 'When is the electoral register updated?', 'radio', 'The electoral register is updated every year inSeptember or October.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(757, 32, 'p12', 'Where does the Scottish Parliament sit?', 'radio', 'In Scotland the elected members, called MSPs, meet in the Scottish Parliament building at Holyrood inEdinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(758, 32, 'p13', 'Which of the following is a ceremonial role to be undertaken by the King?', 'radio', 'The King has important ceremonial roles, such as theopening of the new parliamentary session each year. On this occasion the King makes a speech which summarises the government’s policies for the year ahead.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(759, 32, 'p14', 'How long can you use your driving licence in the UK if you have a licence from another country?', 'radio', 'If you have a licence from another country, you may use it in the UKfor up to 12 months.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(760, 32, 'p15', 'Which Court deals with the most serious civil cases in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'More serious civil cases – for example, when a large amount of compensation is being claimed – are dealt with inthe High Courtof England, Wales and Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(761, 32, 'p16', 'If you are arrested and taken to a police station, a police officer should:', 'radio', 'If you are arrested and taken to a police station, a police officer willtell you the reason for your arrest and you will be able to seek legal advice.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(762, 32, 'p17', 'The UK is one of the five permanent members of the Security Council:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(763, 32, 'p18', 'Which of the following four changes did the Chartists NOT campaign for?', 'radio', 'The Chartists campaigned for every man to have the vote,elections every year, for all regions to be equal in the electoral system, secret ballots, for any man to be able to stand as an MP and for MPs to be paid.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(764, 32, 'p19', 'Which of the following is a criminal offence?', 'radio', 'It is illegal and a criminal offenceto sell tobacco products(for example, cigarettes, cigars, roll-up tobacco)to anyone under the age of 18.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(765, 32, 'p20', 'Which court deals with serious criminal offences in Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, serious criminal offences are tried in front of a judge and a jury in aCrown Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(766, 32, 'p21', 'Which political party does the Speaker represent?', 'radio', 'The Speaker is neutral and does not represent a political party, even though he or she is an MP, represents a constituency and deals with the constituents’ problems like any other MP.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(767, 32, 'p22', 'When was the Scottish Parliament formed?', 'radio', 'The Scottish Parliament was formed in1999.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(768, 32, 'p23', 'Who is the heir to the throne of the UK?', 'radio', 'The King’s eldest son,Prince William (the Prince of Wales), is the heir to the throne.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(769, 33, 'p0', 'Membership to the Commonwealth is compulsory for its members:', 'radio', 'False. Membership to the Commonwealth isvoluntary.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(770, 33, 'p1', 'How many verdicts are possible in trials in Scotland?', 'radio', 'The jury has to listen to the evidence presented at the trial and then decide a verdict of‘guilty’or‘not guilty’based of what they have heard. In Scotland, a third verdict of‘not proven’is also possible.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(771, 33, 'p2', 'Which of the following charities works with sick animals?', 'radio', 'The PDSAis the People’s Dispensary for Sick Animals.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(772, 33, 'p3', 'Which of the following is the responsibility of the Home Secretary?', 'radio', 'The Home Secretary is responsible forcrime, policing and immigration.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(773, 33, 'p4', 'What is the minimum age required for a citizen to stand for public office?', 'radio', 'Most citizens of the UK, the Irish republic or the Commonwealth aged18or over can stand for public office.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(774, 33, 'p5', 'Who makes sure that the opposition has a guaranteed amount of time to debate issues which it chooses during political debates?', 'radio', 'The Speakerkeeps order during political debates to make sure the rules are followed. This includes making sure the opposition has a guaranteed amount of time to debate issues which it chooses.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(775, 33, 'p6', 'Citizens of Liechtenstein can drive in the UK for as long as their driving license is valid:', 'radio', 'True. If your driving licence if from a country in the European Union (EU), Iceland, Liechtenstein or Norway, you can drive in the UK for as long as your licence is valid.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(776, 33, 'p7', 'What is the money raised from the Income Tax used for (choose THREE options)?', 'checkbox', 'Money raised from income tax pays for government services such asroads, education, police and the armed forces.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(777, 33, 'p8', 'When were the Forced Marriage Protection Orders introduced for England, Wales and Northern Ireland, which aimed at protecting a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage?', 'radio', 'Forced Marriage Protection Orders were introduced in2008for England, Wales and Northern Ireland under the Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(778, 33, 'p9', 'In the UK, if the jury finds a defendant guilty, the judge decides the penalty:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(779, 33, 'p10', 'Which of the following countries is a member of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'Bangladeshis a member of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(780, 33, 'p11', 'Which of the following is NOT a principle included in the European Convention of Human Rights?', 'radio', 'Prohibition of  immoral thoughtsis not one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(781, 33, 'p12', 'A system of government where the whole adult population gets a say is known as:', 'radio', 'Democracyis a system of government where the whole adult population gets a say. This might be by direct voting or by choosing representatives to make decisions on their behalf.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(782, 33, 'p13', 'Which of the following statements is correct?', 'radio', 'Arranged marriages refer to marriages where both parties agree to the marriage.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(783, 33, 'p14', 'The devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have the power to legislate on any issues that affect them:', 'radio', 'False. Devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have the power to legislateon certain issues.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(784, 33, 'p15', 'What name is given to the members of the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'All of the electedMPsform the House of Commons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(785, 33, 'p16', 'Which of the following is NOT a role of the King:', 'radio', 'The King receives foreign ambassadors and high commissioners, entertains visiting heads of state, and makes state visits overseas in support of diplomatic and relationships with other counties.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(786, 33, 'p17', 'The Speaker is a neutral MP and does not represent a political party:', 'radio', 'True. The Speaker is neutral and does not represent a political party, even though he or she is an MP, represents a constituency and deals with the constituents’ problems like any other MP.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(787, 33, 'p18', 'How can a person facing domestic violence find a safe place to stay (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'If you are facing domestic violence you can get help from the 24-hour National Domestic Violence Freephone Helpline on 0808 2000 247 at any time, or the police can help you find a safe place to stay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(788, 33, 'p19', 'Who has control over policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security in Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'Policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security all remain undercentral UK governmentcontrol. However, many other public services, such as education, are controlled by the devolved administrations.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(789, 33, 'p20', 'The devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland cannot control policies and laws governing taxation and social security:', 'radio', 'True. Policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security all remain under central UK government control. However, many other public services, such as education, are controlled by the devolved administrations.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(790, 33, 'p21', 'In the UK, brutality and violence in the home is not a crime:', 'radio', 'False. In the UK, brutality and violence in the homeis a serious crime.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(791, 33, 'p22', 'UK laws ensure that people are not treated unfairly in any area of life or work because of their age, disability, sex, pregnancy and maternity, race, religion or belief, sexuality or marital status:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(792, 33, 'p23', 'Since 1997, some powers have been devolved from the central government to give people in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland more control over matters that directly affect them:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(793, 34, 'p0', 'How can you visit the Senedd?', 'radio', 'To make a booking to visit the Senedd, you have tocontact the Senedd Booking Service.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(794, 34, 'p1', 'In which of the following matters the Scottish Parliament CANNOT legislate?', 'radio', 'The matters on which the Scottish Parliament can legislate include: civil and criminal law, health, education, planning and additional tax-raising powers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(795, 34, 'p2', 'Does Britain have a constitutional monarchy?', 'radio', 'True. The UK has a constitutional monarchy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(796, 34, 'p3', 'The devolved administrations of Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland each have their own civil service:', 'radio', 'True. The devolved administrations each have their own civil service.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(797, 34, 'p4', 'Carrying a weapon is a criminal offence, unless it is for self-defence:', 'radio', 'False. It is a criminal offence to carry a weapon of any kind, even if it is for self-defence. This includes a gun, a knife or anything that is made or adapted to cause injury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(798, 34, 'p5', 'Prohibition of thought, conscience and religion is one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights:', 'radio', 'False. Freedom of thought, conscience and religion is one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(799, 34, 'p6', 'Will a non-UK national living in the UK and looking for work, starting work or setting up as self-employed need a National Insurance number?', 'radio', 'True. A non-UK national living in the UK and looking for work, starting work or setting up as self-employed will need a National Insurance number. However, you can start work without one.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(800, 34, 'p7', 'Which of the following is NOT a responsibility of the MPs?', 'radio', 'MPs have a number of different responsibilities. They represent everyone in their constituency, help to create new laws, scrutinize and comment on what the government is doing and debate important national issues.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(801, 34, 'p8', 'The clock tower is named ‘Elizabeth Tower’ in honour of:', 'radio', 'The clock tower is named ‘Elizabeth Tower’ in honour ofQueen Elizabeth II’s Diamond Jubilee in 2012.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(802, 34, 'p9', 'The right to a fair trial is not included amongst the principles of the European Convention of Human Rights:', 'radio', 'False. The right to a fair trial is one of the principles of the European Convention of Human Rights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(803, 34, 'p10', 'Which of the following is NOT classified as a criminal offence in the UK?', 'radio', 'Cases of unfair dismissal or discrimination in the workplace are considered civil offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(804, 34, 'p11', 'The right to life and the right to liberty and security are some of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights:', 'radio', 'This istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `test_id`, `question_id`, `question_text`, `question_type`, `explanation`, `created_at`) VALUES
(805, 34, 'p12', 'When are local elections for councillors held in most local authorities?', 'radio', 'For most local authorities, local elections for councillors are heldin May every year.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(806, 34, 'p13', 'Which of the following is NOT protected by the laws of discrimination?', 'radio', 'UK laws ensure that people are not treated unfairly in any area of life or work because of their age, disability, sex, pregnancy and maternity, race, religion or belief, sexuality or marital status.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(807, 34, 'p14', 'Which of the following countries is NOT a member of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'Greeceis not a member of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(808, 34, 'p15', 'In England, Wales and Scotland, most minor criminal cases are dealt with in a Magistrates’ Court:', 'radio', 'False. In England, Wales andNorthern Ireland, most minor criminal cases are dealt with in a Magistrates’ Court. In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to a Justice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(809, 34, 'p16', 'When did the UK sign the European Convention of Human Rights?', 'radio', 'The UK was one of the first countries to sign the Convention in1950.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(810, 34, 'p17', 'Which of the following is NOT a devolved administration?', 'radio', 'There are three devolved administrations in the UK, this include: the Senedd, the Scottish Parliament and the Northern Ireland Assembly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(811, 34, 'p18', 'What was the name of the European Union when it was first established?', 'radio', 'The European Union (EU), originally calledthe European Economic Community (EEC), was set up by six western European countries (Belgium, France, Germany, Italy, Luxembourg and the Netherlands) who signed the Treaty of Rome on 25 March 1957.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(812, 34, 'p19', 'Which Act incorporated the European Convention of Human Rights into UK law?', 'radio', 'The Human Rights Act 1998incorporated the European Convention of Human Rights into UK law.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(813, 34, 'p20', 'Arranged marriages are not acceptable in the UK:', 'radio', 'False. Arranged marriages, where both parties agree to the marriage, are acceptable in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(814, 34, 'p21', 'Who represents the UK to the rest of the world?', 'radio', 'The Kingrepresents the UK to the rest of the world.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(815, 34, 'p22', 'Who is responsible for managing relationships with foreign countries?', 'radio', 'The Foreign Secretaryis responsible for managing relationships with foreign countries.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(816, 34, 'p23', 'If a husband forces his wife to have sex, he can be charged with rape:', 'radio', 'True. Any man who forces a woman to have sex, including a woman’s husband, can be charged with rape.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(817, 35, 'p0', 'Who were the first people to arrive in Britain in what we call the Stone Age?', 'radio', 'The first people to live in Britain werehunter-gatherers, in what we call the Stone Age.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(818, 35, 'p1', 'When did Britain become permanently separated from the continent by the Channel?', 'radio', 'Britain only became permanently separated from the continent by the Channel about10,000 years ago.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(819, 35, 'p2', 'The Commonwealth has no power over its members and it cannot suspend their membership:', 'radio', 'The Commonwealth has no power over its members, although it can suspend membership.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(820, 35, 'p3', 'Which of the following statements regarding the Black Death is NOT true?', 'radio', 'In 1348, a disease, probably a form of plague, came to Britain. This was known as the Black Death. One third of the population of England died and a similar proportion in Scotland and Wales. This was one of the worst disasters ever to strike Britain. Following the Black Death, the smaller population meant there was less need to grow cereal crops. There were labour shortages and peasants began to demand higher wages.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(821, 35, 'p4', 'Who was reigning in England when Wales became formally united with England by the Act for the Government of Wales?', 'radio', 'During the reign ofHenry VIII, Wales became formally united with England by the Act for the Government of Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(822, 35, 'p5', 'The Elizabethan period is known for the richness of its poetry and drama, especially for the plays and poems of which playwright?', 'radio', 'The Elizabethan period is remembered for the richness of its poetry and drama, especially the plays and poems ofWilliam Shakespeare.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(823, 35, 'p6', 'Which of the following is NOT a fundamental principle of British life?', 'radio', 'The fundamental principles of British life include: tolerance of those with different faiths and beliefs, the rule of law, democracy, individual liberty and participation in community life.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(824, 35, 'p7', 'Which TWO of the following are environmental charities?', 'checkbox', 'The National Trust and Friends of the Earth are environmental charities.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(825, 35, 'p8', 'Which flag has a diagonal red cross on a white ground?', 'radio', 'The cross of St Patrick, patron saint of Ireland, is a diagonal red cross on a white ground.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(826, 35, 'p9', 'Where is the city of Swansea located?', 'radio', 'Swansea is located inWales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(827, 35, 'p10', 'When is Christmas Eve celebrated?', 'radio', 'Christmas Eve is celebrated on the 24th of December.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(828, 35, 'p11', 'Which British sportsman won five consecutive gold medals at the Olympic Games in the rowing category?', 'radio', 'Sir Steve Redgravewon gold medals in rowing in five consecutive Olympic Games and is one of Britain’s greatest Olympians.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(829, 35, 'p12', 'What is the name of the centrepiece to the Remembrance Day service located in Whitehall, London?', 'radio', 'The Cenotaph in Whitehall is the site of the annual Remembrance Day service attended by the King, politicians and foreign ambassadors.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(830, 35, 'p13', 'Who was the inventor of the World Wide Web?', 'radio', 'The inventor of the World Wide Web, Sir Tim Berners-Lee (1955-), is British. Information was successfully transferred via the web for the first time on 25 December 1990.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(831, 35, 'p14', 'What does the UK offer to its residents or citizens (choose FIVE answers)?', 'checkbox', 'The UK offers to its residents or citizens: freedom of belief and religion, freedom of speech, freedom from unfair discrimination, a right to a fair trial and a right to join in the election of a government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(832, 35, 'p15', 'When did the Wars of the Roses start?', 'radio', 'In 1455, a civil war was begun to decide who should be king of England. It was fought between the supporters of two families: the House of Lancaster and the House of York. This war was called the Wars of the Roses, because the symbol of Lancaster was a red rose and the symbol of York was a white rose.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(833, 35, 'p16', 'How many members does the Scottish Parliament have?', 'radio', 'There are 129 members of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs), elected by a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(834, 35, 'p17', 'What does the term ‘coalition’ refer to?', 'radio', 'The government is usually formed by the party that wins the majority of constituencies. If no party wins a majority, two parties may join together to form a coalition.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(835, 35, 'p18', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries in both the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(836, 35, 'p19', 'Pool and darts are traditional pub games.', 'radio', 'True.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(837, 35, 'p20', 'When did the UK formally leave the European Union?', 'radio', 'The UK formally left the European Union on31 January 2020.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(838, 35, 'p21', 'What is the minimum age requirement in the UK to drink wine or beer with a meal provided you are with someone over 18?', 'radio', 'When they are 16, people can drink wine or beer with a meal in a hotel or restaurant (including eating areas in pubs) as long as they are with someone over 18.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(839, 35, 'p22', 'Who is the spiritual leader of the Church of England?', 'radio', 'The spiritual leader of  the Church of England isthe Archbishop of Canterbury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(840, 35, 'p23', 'Civil servants cannot stand for public office:', 'radio', 'Most citizens of the UK, Ireland or the Commonwealth aged 18 or over can stand for public office. There are some exceptions, including: members of the armed forces, civil servants, people found guilty of certain criminal offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(841, 36, 'p0', 'Which Scottish city is known as the home of golf?', 'radio', 'St. Andrews in Scotland is known as the home of golf.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(842, 36, 'p1', 'Which court deals with the most serious cases of children aged 10 to 17 in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in a Youth Court in front of up to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge. The most serious cases will gothe Crown Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(843, 36, 'p2', 'What is the name of the best preserved prehistoric village in northern Europe and which origin traces back to the Stone Age?', 'radio', 'Skara Braeon Orkney, off the north coast of Scotland, is the best preserved prehistoric village in northern Europe, and has helped archaeologists to understand more about how people lived near the end of the Stone Age.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(844, 36, 'p3', 'When was the National Trust founded?', 'radio', 'The National Trust was founded in1895by three volunteers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(845, 36, 'p4', 'After the Black Death, new social classes appeared in England, including owners of large areas of land known as:', 'radio', 'Following the Black Death, the smaller population meant there was less need to grow cereal crops. There were labour shortages and peasants began to demand higher wages. New social classes appeared, including owners of large areas of land (later called thegentry), and people left the countryside to live in the towns. In the towns, growing wealth led to the development of a strong middle class.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(846, 36, 'p5', 'Elizabeth I was the younger daughter of which King?', 'radio', 'Elizabeth I was the younger daughter ofHenry VIII.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(847, 36, 'p6', 'Which of the following operas was written by Gilbert and Sullivan?', 'radio', 'In the 19th century, Gilbert and Sullivan wrote comic operas, often making fun of popular culture and politics. These operas include HMS Pinafore, The Pirates of Penzance andThe Mikado.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(848, 36, 'p7', 'Where is Loch Lomond and the Trossachs National Park located?', 'radio', 'Loch Lomond and the Trossachs National Park is located in thewest of Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(849, 36, 'p8', 'Who is married to the King of the United Kingdom?', 'radio', 'The King of the United Kingdom is married to Camila, the Queen Consort.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(850, 36, 'p9', 'By what TWO other names is the Church of England known?', 'checkbox', 'The official Church of the state is the Church of England (called theAnglican Churchin other countries and theEpiscopal Churchin Scotland and the United States).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(851, 36, 'p10', 'Who was the first British Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The first man to British Prime Minister wasSir Robert Walpole, who was Prime Minister from 1721 to 1742.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(852, 36, 'p11', 'What day does Lent start?', 'radio', 'Lent begins on Ash Wednesday.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(853, 36, 'p12', 'How old do you need to be to apply for a free TV licence?', 'radio', 'Peopleover 75can apply for a free TV licence and blind people can get a 50% discount.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(854, 36, 'p13', 'What time do pubs usually open on Sundays in the UK?', 'radio', 'Pubs are usually open during the day from 11.00 am (12 noon on Sundays).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(855, 36, 'p14', 'What is the official home of the Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The official home of the Prime Minister is 10 Downing Street, in central London, near the Houses of Parliament. He or she also has a country house outside London called Chequers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(856, 36, 'p15', 'When did the Conservative government called a referendum on the UK’s membership of the European Union?', 'radio', 'The Conservative government called a referendum on the UK’s membership of the European Union on the 23rd June 2016.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(857, 36, 'p16', 'Which British sportswoman won two gold medals for running in the 2004 Olympic Games?', 'radio', 'Dame Kelly Holmes won two gold medals for running in the 2004 Olympic Games. She has held a number of British and European records.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(858, 36, 'p17', 'What percentage of the total British population is located in England alone?', 'radio', 'The population is very unequally distributed over the four parts of the UK. England more or less consistently makes up 84% of the total population, Wales around 5%, Scotland just over 8%, and Northern Ireland less than 3%.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(859, 36, 'p18', 'What was the population of the UK in 2010?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 2010 was just over 62 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(860, 36, 'p19', 'Which court deals with cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract and divorce in England and Wales?', 'radio', 'County Courts deal with a wide range of civil disputes. These include people trying to get back money that is owed to them, cases involving personal injury, family matters, breaches of contract, and divorce. In Scotland, most of these matters are dealt with in the Sheriff Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(861, 36, 'p20', 'What is the name of the building where the Scottish Parliament meet?', 'radio', 'In Scotland the elected members, called MSPs, meet in the Scottish Parliament building atHolyroodin Edinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(862, 36, 'p21', 'Which flower is associated with England?', 'radio', 'The rose is the flower associated with England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(863, 36, 'p22', 'Who was Robert Burns?', 'radio', 'Known in Scotland as ‘The Bard’, Robert Burns was aScottish poet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(864, 36, 'p23', 'In which period did British Film studios flourish?', 'radio', 'British film studios flourished in the 1930s.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(865, 37, 'p0', 'What is the capital city of Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'The capital city of Northern Ireland isBelfast.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(866, 37, 'p1', 'What name is given to the day when people play jokes on each other until midday?', 'radio', 'April Fool’s Day, 1 April, is a day when people play jokes on each other until midday. The television and newspapers often have stories that are April Fool jokes.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(867, 37, 'p2', 'Who is the fastest person to have sailed around the world single-handed?', 'radio', 'Dame Ellen MacArthur(1976-) is a yachtswoman and in 2004 became the fastest person to sail around the world singlehanded.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(868, 37, 'p3', 'When did the First World War end?', 'radio', 'The First World War ended at 11.00 amon the 11th November 1918with victory for Britain and its allies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(869, 37, 'p4', 'What are Welsh cakes made of?', 'radio', 'Welsh cakes are a traditional Welsh snack made fromflour, dried fruits and spices, and served either hot or cold.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(870, 37, 'p5', 'Where is the London Eye situated?', 'radio', 'The London Eye is situatedon the southern bank of the River Thamesand is a Ferris wheel that is 443 feet (135 metres) tall.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(871, 37, 'p6', 'What is the relationship between the monarch and the government?', 'radio', 'The monarch has regular meetings with the Prime Minister and can advise, warn and encourage, but the decisions on government policies are made by the Prime Minister and cabinet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(872, 37, 'p7', 'The UK is a ‘constitutional monarchy’:', 'radio', 'The UK has a constitutional monarchy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(873, 37, 'p8', 'What do you need to apply to become a permanent resident or citizen of the UK (Choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'To apply to become a permanent resident or citizen of the UK, you will need to speak and read English and have a good understanding of life in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(874, 37, 'p9', 'Which British scientist was awarded a Nobel Prize for discovering the structure of the DNA molecule?', 'radio', 'The structure of the DNA molecule was discovered in 1953 through work at British universities in London and Cambridge. This discovery contributed to many scientific advances, particularly in medicine and fighting crime.Francis Crick(1916-2004), one of those awarded the Nobel Prize for this discovery, was British.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(875, 37, 'p10', 'Who established the Church of England?', 'radio', 'To divorce his first wife,Henry VIIIneeded the approval of the Pope. When the Pope refused, Henry established the Church of England. In this new church, the king, not the Pope, would have the power to appoint bishops and order how people should worship.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(876, 37, 'p11', 'When does Lent take place?', 'radio', 'The40 days before Easterare known as Lent. It is a time when Christians take time to reflect and prepare for Easter.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(877, 37, 'p12', 'Which of the following national galleries is NOT located in London?', 'radio', 'The National Museum is located in Cardiff, Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(878, 37, 'p13', 'How much can you be fined if you watch TV but do not have a TV licence?', 'radio', 'You will receive a fineup to £1,000if you watch TV but do not have a TV licence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(879, 37, 'p14', 'How old is the clock at the Houses of Parliament in London, also known as ‘Big Ben’?', 'radio', 'Big Ben is the nickname for the great bell of the clock at the House of Parliament in London. The clock is over150 years oldand is a popular tourist attraction.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(880, 37, 'p15', 'The UK was a full member of the European Union but did not use the Euro currency.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(881, 37, 'p16', 'The North Atlantic Treaty Organisation is a group of European and North American countries that was created with which TWO purposes:', 'checkbox', 'NATO is a group of European and North American countries that have agreed to help each other if they come under attack. It also aims to maintain peace between all of its members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(882, 37, 'p17', 'The small claims procedure is used in England and Wales for minor disputes for:', 'radio', 'This procedure is used forclaims of less than £10,000in England and Wales and £3,000 in Scotland and Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(883, 37, 'p18', 'What name is given to the period in the 18th century when new ideas about politics, philosophy and science were developed?', 'radio', 'During the 18th century, new ideas about politics, philosophy and science were developed. This is often called ‘the Enlightenment’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(884, 37, 'p19', 'What is the meaning of ‘Magna Carta’?', 'radio', 'The Magna Carta (which meansthe Great Charter). The Magna Carta established the idea that even the king was subject to the law. It protected the rights of the nobility and restricted the king’s power to collect taxes or to make and change laws.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(885, 37, 'p20', 'When did the Wars of the Roses end?', 'radio', 'The Wars of the Roses ended with the Battle of Bosworth Field in 1485.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(886, 37, 'p21', 'Which of the following is the responsibility of the Chancellor of the Exchequer?', 'radio', 'The Chancellor of the Exchequer is responsible for the economy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(887, 37, 'p22', 'In which British university did Isaac Newton study?', 'radio', 'Isaac Newton studiedat Cambridge University.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(888, 37, 'p23', 'Who invaded England after the Romans?', 'radio', 'The Roman army left Britain in AD 410 to defend other parts of the Roman Empire and never returned. Britain was again invaded by tribes from northern Europe: the Jutes, the Angles and the Saxons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(889, 38, 'p0', 'When did people learn to make bronze?', 'radio', 'Around 4,000 years ago, people learned to make bronze. We call this period the Bronze Age.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(890, 38, 'p1', 'When is the Jewish celebration known as Hanukkah normally celebrated?', 'radio', 'Hanukkah is inNovember or Decemberand is celebrated for eight days.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(891, 38, 'p2', 'What musical award is given during the Mercury Music Prize?', 'radio', 'The Mercury Music Prize is awarded each September for the best album from the UK and Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(892, 38, 'p3', 'Who was Boudicca?', 'radio', 'One of the tribal leaders who fought against the Romans was Boudicca, the queen of the Iceni in what is now eastern England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(893, 38, 'p4', 'Which TWO of the following water sports are popular in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'Sailing continues to be popular in the UK, reflecting its maritime heritage. Rowing is also popular, both as a leisure activity and as a competitive sport.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(894, 38, 'p5', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'Forcing another person to marry is a criminal offence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(895, 38, 'p6', 'In the UK, what should dogs wear in public places?', 'radio', 'All dogs in public places must wear a collar showing the name and address of the owner.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(896, 38, 'p7', 'Where do UK residents need to register their car or motorcycle?', 'radio', 'If you are resident in the UK, your car or motor cycle must be registered at the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(897, 38, 'p8', 'Popular social networking websites in the UK include:', 'radio', 'Social networking websites such asFacebook and Twitterare a popular in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(898, 38, 'p9', 'According to the 2011 Census, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Muslim?', 'radio', 'In the 2011 Census, 59% of people identified themselves as Christian. Much smaller proportions identified themselves as Muslim (4.8%), Hindu (1.5%), Sikh (0.8%), Jewish or Buddhist (both less than 0.5%).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(899, 38, 'p10', 'How often are elections held for the Welsh government?', 'radio', 'The Welsh government has 60 Senedd members (SMs) and elections are held every four years using a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(900, 38, 'p11', 'Who was the British Minister after Margaret Thatcher?', 'radio', 'John Major was Prime Minister after Mrs Thatcher, and helped establish the Northern Ireland peace process.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(901, 38, 'p12', 'What name is given to the person appointed by local authorities to be the ceremonial leader of a particular council?', 'radio', 'Many local authorities appoint amayor, who is the ceremonial leader of the council. In some towns, a mayor is elected to be the effective leader of the administration.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(902, 38, 'p13', 'What is the meaning of the term ‘first past the post’?', 'radio', 'MPs are elected through a system called ‘first past the post’. In each constituency, the candidate who gets the most votes is elected.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(903, 38, 'p14', 'Who defeated Emperor Napoleon at the Battle of Waterloo in 1815?', 'radio', 'In 1815, the French Wars ended with the defeat of the Emperor Napoleon bythe Duke of Wellingtonat the Battle of Waterloo.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(904, 38, 'p15', 'Which court deals with the MOST serious cases in Scotland, such as murder?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, serious cases are heard in a Sheriff Court with either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury. Themost serious casesin Scotland, such as murder, are heard at aHigh Courtwith a judge and jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(905, 38, 'p16', 'What was the symbol of the House of Tudor?', 'radio', 'The symbol of the House of Tudor was a red rose with a white rose inside it as a sign that the Houses of York and Lancaster were now allies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(906, 38, 'p17', 'What animal is represented in the Welsh flag?', 'radio', 'There is also an official Welsh flag, which shows a Welshdragon. The Welsh dragon does not appear on the Union Flag because, when the first Union Flag was created in 1606 from the flags of Scotland and England, the Principality of Wales was already untied with England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(907, 38, 'p18', 'Which famous economist developed ideas about economics during the 18th century and which are still referred to today?', 'radio', 'During the 18th century, new ideas about politics, philosophy and science were developed. This is often called ‘the Enlightenment’. Many of the great thinkers of the Enlightenment were Scottish.Adam Smithdeveloped ideas about economics which are still referred to today.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(908, 38, 'p19', 'Who is the ceremonial head of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'The King is the ceremonial head of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(909, 38, 'p20', 'What time do pubs usually open during the week?', 'radio', 'Pubs are usually open during the day from 11.00 am (12 noon on Sundays).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(910, 38, 'p21', 'In which TWO movie categories does Britain continue to be particularly strong at?', 'checkbox', 'Britain continues to be particularly strong in special effects and animation movies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(911, 38, 'p22', 'Which British artist was a portrait painter who often painted people in country or garden scenarios?', 'radio', 'Thomas Gainsborough (1727-88) was a portrait painter who often painted people in country or garden scenery.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(912, 38, 'p23', 'During which religious celebration do Muslims sacrifice an animal to eat?', 'radio', 'Many Muslims sacrifice an animal to eat during Eid ul Adha.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(913, 39, 'p0', 'How old do you need to be to be able to play the National Lottery?', 'radio', 'People under 18 are not allowed to participate in the National Lottery.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(914, 39, 'p1', 'Where is the five-day race meeting attended by members of the Royal Family and known as Royal Ascot celebrated?', 'radio', 'Royal Ascot, the five-day race meeting  attended by members of the Royal Family, takes place in Berkshire.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(915, 39, 'p2', 'Who was the first person to lead a Roman invasion in Britain in 55 BC?', 'radio', 'Julius Caesar led a Roman invasion of Britain in 55 BC.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(916, 39, 'p3', 'Who wrote ‘The Lord of the Rings’?', 'radio', 'The Lord of the Rings was written by JRR Tolkien.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(917, 39, 'p4', 'Which court deals with minor criminal cases in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, most minor criminal cases are dealt with in a Magistrates’ Court. In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to a Justice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(918, 39, 'p5', 'What name is given to the tombs where people buried their dead during the Bronze Age?', 'radio', 'During the Bronze Age people lived in roundhouses and buried their dead in tombs calledround barrows.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(919, 39, 'p6', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly cannot make decisions on:', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly can make decisions on issues such as education, agriculture, the environment, health and social services. It cannot make decisions on defence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(920, 39, 'p7', 'According to the 2011 Census, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Buddhist?', 'radio', 'In the 2011 Census, 59% of people identified themselves as Christian. Much smaller proportions identified themselves as Muslim (4.8%), Hindu (1.5%), Sikh (0.8%), Jewish or Buddhist (both less than 0.5%).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(921, 39, 'p8', 'In which category did Jayne Torvill and Christopher Dean win gold medals at the Olympic Games in 1984?', 'radio', 'Jayne Torvill and Christopher Dean won gold medals for ice dancing at the Olympic Games in 1984 and is one of Britain’s greatest Olympians.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(922, 39, 'p9', 'What is the first verse of the National Anthem of the UK ‘God save the King’?', 'radio', 'The first verse of the National Anthem of the UK is ‘God save our gracious King!.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(923, 39, 'p10', 'Which of the following is NOT a British invention of the 20th century?', 'radio', 'Radioactivity is not a British invention.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(924, 39, 'p11', 'Which British Prime Minister was famous for the speech ‘I have nothing to offer but blood, toil, tears and sweat’?', 'radio', 'During the Second World War, Winston Churchill made many famous speeches including lines which you may still hear:  ‘I have nothing to offer but blood, toil, tears and sweat’. This was Churchill’s first speech to the House of Commons after he became Prime Minister, 1940.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(925, 39, 'p12', 'Which of the following countries did NOT belong to the Allies during World War I?', 'radio', 'Bulgaria was not part of the Allies during the First World War.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(926, 39, 'p13', 'Which TWO of the following charities work with homeless people?', 'checkbox', 'Charities that work with homeless people include Crisis and Shelter.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(927, 39, 'p14', 'Which flower is associated with Scotland?', 'radio', 'Thethistleis the flower associated with Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(928, 39, 'p15', 'What is the money from TV licences used for?', 'radio', 'The money from TV licences is used to pay for the British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC). This is a public service broadcaster providing television and radio programmes. The BBC is the largest broadcaster in the world. It is the only wholly state-funded media organisation that is independent of government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(929, 39, 'p16', 'Members of the Welsh government are elected every four years on the basis of:', 'radio', 'The Welsh government and the Senedd are based in Cardiff, the capital city of Wales. There are 60 members of the Senedd (SMs) and elections are held every four years using a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(930, 39, 'p17', 'What is the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'The Commonwealth is an association of countries that support each other and work together towards shared goals in democracy and development. Most member states were once part of the British Empire, although a few countries which were not have also joined.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(931, 39, 'p18', 'Which famous architect designed St Paul’s Cathedral after it was destroyed by a fire in 1666?', 'radio', 'In 1666, a great fire destroyed much of the city of London, including many churches and St Paul’s Cathedral. London was rebuilt with a new St Paul’s, which was designed by a famous architect, Sir Christopher Wren.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(932, 39, 'p19', 'Which of the following is a fundamental principle of life in the UK?', 'radio', 'The fundamental principles of British life include: democracy, the rule of law, individual liberty, tolerance of those with different faiths and beliefs and participation in community life.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(933, 39, 'p20', 'Which of the following countries belongs to the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'Mozambique.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(934, 39, 'p21', 'Who has to pay national insurance contributions in the UK?', 'radio', 'Almost everybody in the UK who is in paid work, including self-employed people, must pay National Insurance Contributions.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(935, 39, 'p22', 'A good way to support your local community is to shop for products locally.', 'radio', 'This statement is TRUE.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(936, 39, 'p23', 'Where is the centrepiece to the Remembrance Day service known as Cenotaph located?', 'radio', 'The Cenotaph, the Centrepiece to the Remembrance Day service, is located in Whitehall, London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(937, 40, 'p0', 'Which of the following territories does not belong to Great Britain?', 'radio', '‘Great Britain’ refers only to England, Scotland and Wales, not to Northern Ireland. The official name of the country is the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(938, 40, 'p1', 'Who was the first Briton to win the ‘Tour de France’?', 'radio', 'Bradley Wiggins became the first Briton to win the ‘Tour de France’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(939, 40, 'p2', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'The English language has many accents and dialects.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(940, 40, 'p3', 'How old do you need to be to go into betting shops or gambling clubs?', 'radio', 'In the UK, you have to be 18 to go into betting shops or gambling clubs.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(941, 40, 'p4', 'What do Ian McEwan, Hilary Mantel and Julian Barnes have in common?', 'radio', 'The Man Booker Prize for Fiction is awarded annually for the best fiction novel written by an author from the Commonwealth, Ireland or Zimbabwe. It has been awarded since 1968. Past winners include Ian McEwan, Hilary Mantel and Julian Barnes.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(942, 40, 'p5', 'In Northern Ireland members of the Legislative Assembly are elected on the basis of:', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly has 90 elected members, known as MLAs (members of the Legislative Assembly). They are elected with a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(943, 40, 'p6', 'How can MPs be contacted (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'You can contact MPs by letter or telephone at their constituency office, or at their office in the House of Commons: The House of Commons, Westminster, London SW1A OAA, telephone 0207729 3000.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(944, 40, 'p7', 'What did the’Bill of Rights’ confirm in 1689?', 'radio', 'The Bill of Rights, 1689, confirmed the rights of Parliament and the limits of the king’s power. Parliament took control of who could be monarch and declared that the king or queen must be a Protestant.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(945, 40, 'p8', 'Who designed the Clifton Suspension Bridge located over the Avon George?', 'radio', 'The Clifton Suspension Bridge was designed by Isambard Kingdom Brunel.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(946, 40, 'p9', 'Does Britain have a written constitution?', 'radio', 'The British constitution is not written down in any single document, and therefore it is described as ‘unwritten’. This is mainly because the UK, unlike America or France, has never had a revolution which led permanently to a totally new system of government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(947, 40, 'p10', 'What was the estimated population of the British Empire during the Victorian period?', 'radio', 'During the Victorian period, the British Empire grew to cover all of India, Australia and large parts of Africa. It became the largest empire the world has ever seen, with an estimated population of more than 400 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(948, 40, 'p11', 'Which of the following countries was NOT part of the Allied Powers during the First World War?', 'radio', 'Bulgaria formed part of the Central Powers during the First World War.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(949, 40, 'p12', 'How many times have the Olympic Games been hosted in the UK?', 'radio', 'The UK has hosted the Olympic games on three occasions: 1908, 1948 and 2012.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(950, 40, 'p13', 'When were films first shown publicly in the UK?', 'radio', 'Films were first shown publicly in the UK in 1896 and film screenings very quickly became popular.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(951, 40, 'p14', 'What is the name of the building where the Welsh government members meet?', 'radio', 'Elected members of the Welsh government meet at the Senedd in Cardiff, the capital city of Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(952, 40, 'p15', 'Where is the city of Southampton located?', 'radio', 'Southampton is located in England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(953, 40, 'p16', 'When did the First World War finish?', 'radio', 'The First World War ended at 11.00 am on 11th November 1918 with victory for Britain and its allies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(954, 40, 'p17', 'Florence Nightingale was known for her work on:', 'radio', 'Florence Nightingale is often regarded as the founder of modern nursing.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(955, 40, 'p18', 'Which Act abolished slavery throughout the British Empire in 1833?', 'radio', 'In 1833 the Emancipation Act abolished slavery throughout the British Empire. The Royal Navy stopped slave ships from other countries, freed the slaves and punished the slave traders.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(956, 40, 'p19', 'How long does Diwali last for?', 'radio', 'Diwali normally falls in October or November and lasts for five days.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(957, 40, 'p20', 'Who became King of Britain when Queen Anne died in 1714?', 'radio', 'When Queen Anne died in 1714, Parliament chose a German, George I, to be the next king, because he was Anne’s nearest Protestant relative.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(958, 40, 'p21', 'What was the population of the UK in 2005?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 2005 was just under 60 million people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(959, 40, 'p22', 'When did the ‘Habeas Corpus Act’ become law?', 'radio', 'The Habeas Corpus Act became law in 1679.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(960, 40, 'p23', 'Who discovered the penicillin in 1928?', 'radio', 'Alexander Fleming was researching influenza (the ‘flu’) in 1928 when he discovered penicillin.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(961, 41, 'p0', 'During the Middle Ages, England was an important trading nation and people came to England from abroad to trade and also to work. Where did glass manufacturers come from?', 'radio', 'During the Middle Ages people came to England from abroad to trade and also to work, such as weavers from France, engineers from Germany,glass manufacturers from Italyand canal builders from Holland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(962, 41, 'p1', 'Where can people facing domestic violence get help from?', 'radio', 'People facing domestic violence can get help from a solicitor orthe Citizens Advice Bureau.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(963, 41, 'p2', 'Which American President worked closely with Margaret Thatcher?', 'radio', 'Margaret Thatcher worked closely with the United States President,Ronald Reagan, and was one of the first Western leaders to recognise and welcome the changes in the leadership of the Soviet Union which eventually led to the end of the Cold War.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(964, 41, 'p3', 'People might be taken to court if they owe money to someone.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(965, 41, 'p4', 'Who was the first Archbishop of Canterbury?', 'radio', 'St Augustine led missionaries from Rome, who spread Christianity in the south.St Augustinebecame the first Archbishop of Canterbury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(966, 41, 'p5', 'How many members does a jury have in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland a jury has12 members, and in Scotland a jury has 15 members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(967, 41, 'p6', 'What is tested with a driving test (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'To get a UK driving licence you must pass a driving test, which tests both your knowledge and your practical skills.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(968, 41, 'p7', 'What is the role of the Speaker?', 'radio', 'The Speaker keeps order during political debates to make sure the rules are followed.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(969, 41, 'p8', 'Which of the following statements is FALSE regarding Youth Courts?', 'radio', 'They are used for trials of young people aged 10 to 17.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(970, 41, 'p9', 'Which TWO films were directed by David Lean?', 'checkbox', 'David Lean directed Brief Encounter (1945) and Lawrence of Arabia (1962).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(971, 41, 'p10', 'Which of the following venues is located in Glasgow?', 'radio', 'The Scottish Exhibition and Conference Centre (SEC Centre) is located in Glasgow.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(972, 41, 'p11', 'How many British casualties were recorded during the first day of the British attack of the Somme in July 1916 during the First World War?', 'radio', 'The British attack of the Somme in July 1916, resulted in about60,000 British casualtieson the first day alone.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(973, 41, 'p12', 'The Welsh dragon on the Welsh flag does not appear on the Union Flag because, when the first Union Flag was created in 1606 from the flags of Scotland and England, the Principality of Wales was already untied with England:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(974, 41, 'p13', 'Which two countries developed the ‘Concorde’ aircraft?', 'radio', 'Britain and France developed the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner, Concorde.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(975, 41, 'p14', 'What was the population of the UK in 1801?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 1801 was8 millionpeople.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(976, 41, 'p15', 'Where is there UK geographically located?', 'radio', 'The UK is located in thenorth west of Europe.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(977, 41, 'p16', 'What is the main function of the Council of Europe?', 'radio', 'The Council of Europe is responsible for the protection and promotion of human rights in its member countries.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(978, 41, 'p17', 'Sir Alfred Hitchcock was an important British film director', 'radio', 'Eminent directors included Sir Alexander Korda and Sir Alfred Hitchcock, who later left for Hollywood and remained an important film director until his death in 1980.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(979, 41, 'p18', 'Which Scottish physician and researcher co-discovered the insulin used to treat diabetes?', 'radio', 'The Scottish physician and researcherJohn Macleodwas the co-discoverer of insulin, used to treat diabetes.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(980, 41, 'p19', 'Who was voted the greatest Briton of all time in 2002?', 'radio', 'Winston Churchillin 2002 was voted the greatest Briton of all time by the public.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(981, 41, 'p20', 'When is St George’s Day, patron of England?', 'radio', 'St George’s Day, patron of England is celebrated on the23rd of April.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(982, 41, 'p21', 'Which TWO of the following responsibilities will you have as a permanent resident or citizen of the UK?', 'checkbox', 'Respect and obey the law and look after the area in which you live and the environment are the correct answers.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(983, 41, 'p22', 'Which TWO of the following social laws were liberalised during the ‘Swinging Sixties’?', 'checkbox', 'The law of abortion and the law of divorce were liberalised during the ‘Swinging Sixties’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(984, 41, 'p23', 'Who was the mother of Elizabeth I?', 'radio', 'Anne Boleynand Henry VIII had one daughter, Elizabeth I.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(985, 42, 'p0', 'Who was the first wife of Henry VIII?', 'radio', 'Catherine of Aragonwas the first wife of Henry VIII.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(986, 42, 'p1', 'Which of the following flags is not represented in the union flag?', 'radio', 'TheWelsh flagdoes not appear on the Union Flag because, when the first Union Flag was created in 1606 from the flags of Scotland and England, the Principality of Wales was already untied with England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(987, 42, 'p2', 'When does the Edinburgh Festival take place?', 'radio', 'The Edinburgh Festival takes place in Edinburgh, Scotland,every summer.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(988, 42, 'p3', 'When did ‘the Concorde’ aircraft fly for the first time?', 'radio', 'The ‘Concorde’, the world’s only supersonic passenger aircraft, first flew in1969.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(989, 42, 'p4', 'By which other name is the Conservative Party also known as?', 'radio', 'The modern Conservative Party is still sometimes referred to as‘The Tories’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(990, 42, 'p5', 'When was the Northern Ireland Parliament established for the first time?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Parliament was first established in1922.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(991, 42, 'p6', 'What is the opposition?', 'radio', 'The second-largest party in the House of Commons is called the opposition.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(992, 42, 'p7', 'Which two languages combined form the basis of the English language?', 'radio', 'After the Norman Conquest, the king and his noblemen had spoken Norman French and the peasants had continued to speak Anglo-Saxon. Gradually these two languages combined to become one English language.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(993, 42, 'p8', 'Which THREE of the following are known to be main parts of the British government?', 'checkbox', 'In the UK, there are several different parts of government. The main ones are: the monarchy, the Parliament (the House of Commons and the House of Lords),  the Prime Minister, the cabinet, the judiciary (courts), the police, the civil service and the local government.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(994, 42, 'p9', 'When did Adolf Hitler come to power in Germany?', 'radio', 'Adolf Hitler came to power in Germany in1933.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(995, 42, 'p10', 'Who invented the hovercraft?', 'radio', 'Sir Christopher Cockerell(1910-99), a British inventor, invented the hovercraft in the 1950s.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(996, 42, 'p11', 'Which court deals with serious criminal offences in Wales?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, serious criminal offences are tried in front of a judge and a jury in a Crown Court. In Scotland, serious cases are heard in a Sheriff Court with either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(997, 42, 'p12', 'What is the minimum age requirement to buy alcohol in a pub or night club in the UK?', 'radio', 'To buy alcohol in a pub or night club you must be18 or over, but people under that age may be allowed in some pubs with an adult.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(998, 42, 'p13', 'What is the coin with the highest value in the UK?', 'radio', 'The coin with the highest value in the UK is the£2coin.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(999, 42, 'p14', 'When were Protection Orders to protect a person from being forced into a marriage introduced in Scotland?', 'radio', 'Forced Marriage Protection Orders were introduced in 2008 for England, Wales and Northern Ireland under the Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007. Court orders can be obtained to protect a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage. Similar Protection Orders were introduced in Scotland inNovember 2011.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1000, 42, 'p15', 'Which TWO of the following are famous horse racing events in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'Famous horse-racing events in the UK includeRoyal Ascotandthe Grand National.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1001, 42, 'p16', 'Which of the following events relates to the German bombing of London and other British cities at night time during the World War II?', 'radio', 'The Blitzrelates to the German bombing of London and other British cities at night time during the World War II', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1002, 42, 'p17', 'Who wrote an oratorio called ‘Messiah’, which is regularly sung by choirs at Easter time?', 'radio', 'George Frederick Handelwrote an oratorio, Messiah, which is sung regularly by choirs, often at Easter time.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1003, 42, 'p18', 'When did hereditary peers lose the automatic right to attend the House of Lords?', 'radio', 'Since1999, hereditary peers have lost the automatic right to attend the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1004, 42, 'p19', 'Which of the following is England’s largest national park?', 'radio', 'The Lake Districtis England’s largest national park.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1005, 42, 'p20', 'Which of the following social changes took place during the ‘Swinging Sixties’?', 'radio', 'The position of women in the workplace was improved during the ‘Swinging Sixties’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1006, 42, 'p21', 'Where was Emmeline Pankhurst born?', 'radio', 'Emmeline Pankhurst was born inManchesterin 1858.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1007, 42, 'p22', 'Which of the following is a traditional English food?', 'radio', 'Roast beefis a traditional English food.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1008, 42, 'p23', 'What are pantomimes based on?', 'radio', 'Pantomimes are based onfairy storiesand are light-hearted plays with music and comedy, enjoyed by family audiences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1009, 43, 'p0', 'What was inscribed in the first coins to be minted in Britain during the Iron Age?', 'radio', 'The people of the Iron Age made the first coins to be minted in Britain, some inscribed withthe names of Iron Age kings.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1010, 43, 'p1', 'What name is given to the Church of England in Scotland and the United States?', 'radio', 'The Church of England is calledthe Episcopal Churchin Scotland and the United States.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `test_id`, `question_id`, `question_text`, `question_type`, `explanation`, `created_at`) VALUES
(1011, 43, 'p2', 'Who directed the movie ‘Four Weddings and a Funeral’ in 1994?', 'radio', 'Four Weddings and a Funeral (1994) was directed byMike Newell.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1012, 43, 'p3', 'What was the population of the UK in 1951?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 1951 was50 millionpeople.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1013, 43, 'p4', 'Which TWO religions celebrate Diwali?', 'checkbox', 'Diwali is celebrated byHindus and Sikhs. It normally falls in October or November and lasts for five days. It is also often called the Festival of Lights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1014, 43, 'p5', 'Which of the following statements is true?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports called Hansard.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1015, 43, 'p6', 'In Northern Ireland, a newly qualified driver must display an R plate for one year after passing the test.', 'radio', 'This statement isTRUE.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1016, 43, 'p7', 'When did Emmeline Pankhurst set up the women’s Franchise League, which fought to get the vote in local elections for married women?', 'radio', 'Emmeline Pankhurst was born in Manchester in 1858. She set up the women’s Franchise League in1889, which fought to get the vote in local elections for married women. In 1903 she helped found the Women’s Social and Political Union (WSPU).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1017, 43, 'p8', 'How many ski centres are there in Scotland?', 'radio', 'There arefiveski centres in Scotland, as well as Europe’s longest dry ski slope near Edinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1018, 43, 'p9', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries in the House of Commons but not in the House of Lords:', 'radio', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries in both the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1019, 43, 'p10', 'Which is the oldest tennis tournament in the world?', 'radio', 'The most famous tournament hosted in Britain isThe Wimbledon Championships, which takes place each year at the All England Lawn Tennis and Croquet Club. It is the oldest tennis tournament in the world and the only ‘Grand Slam’ event played on grass.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1020, 43, 'p11', 'Which of the following is a British invention of the 20th century?', 'radio', 'TheHarrier jump jet, an aircraft capable of taking off vertically, is a British invention of the 20th century.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1021, 43, 'p12', 'Churchill was the son of a politician and, before becoming a Conservative MP in 1900, was a soldier and journalist.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1022, 43, 'p13', 'During the 17th century there were two main groups in Parliament, which were known as:', 'radio', 'During the 17th century there were two main groups in Parliament, known asthe Whigs and the Tories.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1023, 43, 'p14', 'Where is the ‘Eden Project’ located?', 'radio', 'The Eden Project is located inCornwall, in the south west of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1024, 43, 'p15', 'When was the Women’s Social and Political Union (WSPU) established?', 'radio', 'Emmeline Pankhurst was born in Manchester in 1858. She set up the women’s Franchise League in 1889, which fought to get the vote in local elections for married women. In1903she helped found the Women’s Social and Political Union (WSPU).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1025, 43, 'p16', 'Which of the following is a traditional food from Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'Ulster fry– a fried meal with bacon, eggs, sausage, black pudding, tomatoes, mushrooms, soda bread and potato bread – is a traditional food from Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1026, 43, 'p17', 'Who is the author of the murder mystery play ‘The Mousetrap’?', 'radio', 'The Mousetrap, a murder-mystery play byDame Agatha Christie, has been running in the west end since 1952 and has had the longest initial run of any show in history.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1027, 43, 'p18', 'Under which Act was the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland created?', 'radio', 'In 1801, Ireland became unified with England, Scotland and Wales afterthe Act of Unionof 1800. This created the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1028, 43, 'p19', 'When was the voting age reduced to 18 for men and women?', 'radio', 'In1969, the voting age was reduced to 18 for men and women.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1029, 43, 'p20', 'When is April Fool’s Day?', 'radio', 'April Fool’s Day is on the1st of April.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1030, 43, 'p21', 'Where is the city of Bradford located?', 'radio', 'Bradford is located inEngland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1031, 43, 'p22', 'Which flag comprises a red cross on a white ground?', 'radio', 'The cross of St George, patron saint of England, is a red cross on a white ground.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1032, 43, 'p23', 'When did the first farmers arrive in Britain?', 'radio', 'The first farmers arrived in Britain6,000 years ago.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1033, 44, 'p0', 'In which English county is the monument of Stonehenge located?', 'radio', 'The ancestors of the first farmers probably came from south-east Europe. These people built houses, tombs and monuments on the land. One of these monuments, Stonehenge, still stands in what is now the English county ofWiltshire.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1034, 44, 'p1', 'What is the best-known work from Robert Burns?', 'radio', 'Burns’ best-known work is probably the songAuld Lang Syne, which is sung by people in the UK and other countries when they are celebrating the New Year (or Hogmanay as it is called in Scotland).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1035, 44, 'p2', 'Which of the following crosses does NOT form part of the Union Flag?', 'radio', 'The cross of St David, patron saint of Wales does not form part of the Union Flag because, when the first Union Flag was created in 1606 from the flags of Scotland and England, the Principality of Wales was already untied with England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1036, 44, 'p3', 'What day is Halloween celebrated?', 'radio', 'Halloween is celebrated on the31st of October.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1037, 44, 'p4', 'Who was the first British distance runner to win a gold medal in the Olympic games in the 10,000 metres?', 'radio', 'Mo Farah(1983-) is a British distance runner, born in Somalia. He won gold medals in the 2012 Olympics for the 5,000 and 10,000 metres and is the first Briton to win the Olympic gold medal in the 10,000 metres.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1038, 44, 'p5', 'Which of the following statements is TRUE?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, the 31st December is called Hogmanay and 2 January is also a public holiday. For some Scottish people, Hogmanay is a bigger holiday than Christmas.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1039, 44, 'p6', 'Light-hearted plays with music and comedy, which are enjoyed by family audiences and based on fairy stories are known as:', 'radio', 'Many theatres produce apantomimeat Christmas time. They are based on fairy stories and are light-plays with music and comedy, enjoyed by family audiences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1040, 44, 'p7', 'What British actor was best known for his roles in various Shakespeare plays?', 'radio', 'The Laurence Olivier Awards take place annually at different venues in London. There are a variety of categories, including best director, best actor and best actress. The awards are named after the British actorSir Laurence Olivier, late Lord Olivier, who was best known for his roles in various Shakespeare plays.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1041, 44, 'p8', 'Who built the Tower of London after becoming king in 1066?', 'radio', 'The Tower of London was first built byWilliam the Conquerorafter he became king in 1066.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1042, 44, 'p9', 'Who succeeded David Cameron as Prime Minister after the referendum on the UK’s membership of the European Union?', 'radio', 'David Cameron was succeeded as Prime Minister after the Brexit referendum byTheresa Mayon 13 July 2016.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1043, 44, 'p10', 'Who composed a suite of pieces themed around the planets and the solar system called ‘The Planets’?', 'radio', 'Important British composers includeGustav Holst, whose work includes The Planets, a suite of pieces themed around the planets and the solar system.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1044, 44, 'p11', 'What was the population of the UK in 1998?', 'radio', 'The population of the UK in 1998 was57 millionpeople.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1045, 44, 'p12', 'Who is the chief officer of the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'Debates in the House of Commons are chaired bythe Speaker. This person is the chief officer of the House of Commons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1046, 44, 'p13', 'What characterises the British constitution?', 'radio', 'The British constitution is not written down in any single document, and therefore it is described as ‘unwritten’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1047, 44, 'p14', 'How old was Queen Victoria when she became Queen in 1837?', 'radio', 'In 1837, Queen Victoria became queen of the UK at the age of18.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1048, 44, 'p15', 'When did the First World War start?', 'radio', 'On 28 June1914, Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria was assassinated. This set off a chain of events leading to the First World War (1914-18).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1049, 44, 'p16', 'Who forms the judiciary?', 'radio', 'Judges (who are together called ‘the judiciary’) are responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1050, 44, 'p17', 'Which of the following is a musical venue located in London?', 'radio', 'There are many large venues that host music events throughout the year, such as:The O2in Greenwich, south-east London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1051, 44, 'p18', 'Who directed the movie ‘The Killing Fields’ in 1984?', 'radio', 'The Killing Fields (1984) was directed byRoland Joffé.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1052, 44, 'p19', 'Which TWO of the following castles are located in Scotland?', 'checkbox', 'Inveraray CastleandCrathes Castleare located in Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1053, 44, 'p20', 'Which battle signified the end of the Wars of the Roses?', 'radio', 'The Wars of the Roses ended withthe Battle of Bosworth Fieldin 1485.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1054, 44, 'p21', 'Which court deals with minor criminal offences in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to aJustice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1055, 44, 'p22', 'If an MP dies or resigns, there will be a fresh election, which is known as:', 'radio', 'If an MP dies or resigns, there will be a fresh election, called aby-election, in his or her constituency.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1056, 44, 'p23', 'A person who has not paid enough National Insurance contributions will not be able to receive certain contributory benefits including (choose TWO options):', 'checkbox', 'Anyone who does not pay enough National Insurance Contributions will not be able to receive certain contributory benefits such asJobseeker’s Allowance or a full state retirement pension.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1057, 45, 'p0', 'Who succeeded Theresa May as Prime Minister on the 24th July 2019?', 'radio', 'Theresa May was succeeded byBoris Johnsonon 24 July 2019.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1058, 45, 'p1', 'What name is given to the period of rapid development of industry in Britain in the 18th and 19th centuries?', 'radio', 'The Industrial Revolutionwas the rapid development of industry in Britain in the 18th and 19th centuries.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1059, 45, 'p2', 'During the slave trade, slaves were taken from West Africa to America and the Caribbean to work on tobacco and sugar plantations.', 'radio', 'This statement isTRUE.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1060, 45, 'p3', 'Who was responsible for the construction of the Great Western Railway?', 'radio', 'Isambard Kingdom Brunelwas responsible for constructing the Great Western Railway, which was the first major railway built in Britain.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1061, 45, 'p4', 'In which of the following areas has the Senedd the power to make laws (choose four answers)?', 'checkbox', 'The Senedd has the power to make laws in 21 areas, including: education and training, health and social services, economic development and housing.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1062, 45, 'p5', 'How many members comprise the UN Security Council?', 'radio', 'There are15 memberson the UN Security Council, which recommends action when there are international crises and threats to peace.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1063, 45, 'p6', 'Which TWO of the following forts form part of Hadrian’s Wall?', 'checkbox', 'Parts of Hadrian’s Wall include the forts ofHousesteads and Vindolanda.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1064, 45, 'p7', 'Members of the Welsh government can speak in either English or Welsh, but all of the Senedd’s publications have to be in English:', 'radio', 'Members of the Welsh government can speak in either English or Welsh, and all publications of the Senedd’s publications are in both languages.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1065, 45, 'p8', 'Why did Elizabeth I keep her cousin Mary prisoner for 20 years?', 'radio', 'Elizabeth suspected Mary of wanting to take over the English throne, and kept her prisoner for 20 years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1066, 45, 'p9', 'What was the name of the first cloned mammal?', 'radio', 'In 1996, two British scientists, Sir Ian Wilmot and Keith Campbell, led a team which was the first to succeed in cloning a mammal,Dollythe sheep.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1067, 45, 'p10', 'Who is responsible for the creation of the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms?', 'radio', 'The Council of Europehas no power to make laws but draws up conventions and charters, the most well-known of which is the European Convention on Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1068, 45, 'p11', 'Who became Prime Minister of the UK in May 1940?', 'radio', 'Churchillwas the son of a politician and, before becoming a Conservative MP in 1900, was a soldier and journalist. In May 1940 he became Prime Minister.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1069, 45, 'p12', 'Members of the House of Lords may stand for election to the House of Commons and are eligible for all public offices:', 'radio', 'Members of the House of Lords may not stand for election to the House of Commons but are eligible for all other public offices.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1070, 45, 'p13', 'What can you find at the ‘Eden Project’?', 'radio', 'The Eden Project is located in Cornwall, in the south west of England. Its biomes, which are likegiant greenhouses, house plants from all over the world. The Eden Project is also a charity which runs environmental and social projects internationally.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1071, 45, 'p14', 'What TWO names are given to the people who give tours at the Tower of London?', 'checkbox', 'Tours to the Tower of London are given by theYeoman Warders, also known asBeefeaters, who tell visitors about the building’s history.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1072, 45, 'p15', 'Which of the following is a traditional Scottish food?', 'radio', 'Haggis– a sheep’s stomach stuffed with offal, suet, onions and oatmeal – is a traditional Scottish food.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1073, 45, 'p16', 'How often do the Laurence Olivier Awards take place?', 'radio', 'The Laurence Olivier Awards take placeannuallyat different venues in London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1074, 45, 'p17', 'When is Valentine’s Day?', 'radio', 'Valentine’s Day is celebrated on the14th of February.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1075, 45, 'p18', 'When is St Patrick’s Day, patron to of Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'St Patrick’s Day, patron to of Northern Ireland is on the17th of March.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1076, 45, 'p19', 'What does the term ‘PDSA’ stand for?', 'radio', '‘PDSA’ stands forPeople’s Dispensary for Sick Animals.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1077, 45, 'p20', 'Which of the following TWO islands are ‘Crown dependencies’?', 'checkbox', 'There are several islands which are closely linked with the UK but are not part of it:the Channel Islands and the Isle of Man. These have their own governments and are called ‘Crown dependencies’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1078, 45, 'p21', 'When did English settlers begin to colonise the eastern coast of America?', 'radio', 'In Elizabeth I’s time, English settlers first began to colonise the eastern coast of America.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1079, 45, 'p22', 'When did the Black Death come to England?', 'radio', 'In1348, a disease, probably a form of plague, came to Britain. This was known as the Black Death.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1080, 45, 'p23', 'What is the name of the annual event that gives awards in a range of musical categories, such as best British group and best British solo artist?', 'radio', 'The Brit Awardsis an annual event that gives awards in a range of categories, such as best British group and best British solo artist.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1081, 46, 'p0', 'What name is given to the elected members of the Welsh government?', 'radio', 'In Wales the elected members are known asSMs or Senedd Members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1082, 46, 'p1', 'How often do the ministers that form the Cabinet meet to make important decisions about government policy?', 'radio', 'The cabinet is a committee which usually meetsweeklyand makes important decisions about government policy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1083, 46, 'p2', 'How many Welsh-language channels are there in Wales?', 'radio', 'There isoneWelsh-language channel in Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1084, 46, 'p3', 'What is the nickname for the great bell of the clock at the Houses of Parliament in London?', 'radio', 'Big Benis the nickname for the great bell of the clock at the House of Parliament in London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1085, 46, 'p4', 'How many countries are members of the United Nations?', 'radio', 'The UK is part of the United Nations (UN), an international organization withmore than 190 countriesas members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1086, 46, 'p5', 'Which of the following statements is true?', 'radio', 'The police force is a public service that helps and protects everyone, no matter what their background or where they live.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1087, 46, 'p6', 'What is the system by which the income tax is automatically taken from the employee’s income by their employer and paid directly to HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC)?', 'radio', 'For most people, the right amount of income tax is automatically taken from their income from employment by their employer and paid directly to HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC), the government department that collects taxes. This system is called“Pay As You Earn” (PAYE).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1088, 46, 'p7', 'How many British casualties were recorded during the First World War?', 'radio', 'During the First World War millions of people were killed or wounded, withmore than 2 million British casualties.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1089, 46, 'p8', 'Why did Henry VIII decide to divorce Catherine of Aragon?', 'radio', 'When Catherine was too old to give him another child, Henry VIII decided to divorce her, hoping that another wife would give him a son to be his heir.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1090, 46, 'p9', 'How many local authorities are there in London?', 'radio', 'London has33 local authorities, with the Greater London Authority and the Mayor of London coordinating policies across the capital.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1091, 46, 'p10', 'When did British combat troops leave Iraq?', 'radio', 'British combat troops left Iraq in2009.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1092, 46, 'p11', 'Where is the Parliament of the UK?', 'radio', 'The UK is governed by the parliament sitting inWestminster.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
