(1097, 46, 'p16', 'In which city is the Welsh government building, also known as Senedd, located?', 'radio', 'In Wales the elected members, known as SMs, meet at the Senedd inCardiff Bay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1098, 46, 'p17', 'What architectural style became popular in the 19th century?', 'radio', 'In the 19th century, themedieval ’gothic’ stylebecame popular again. As cities expanded, many great public buildings were built in this style. The Houses of Parliament and St Pancras Station were built at this time, as were the town halls in cities such as Manchester and Sheffield.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1099, 46, 'p18', 'Which of the following gardens is NOT located in England?', 'radio', 'There are famous gardens to visit throughout the UK, including Kew Gardens, Sissinghurst and Hidcote in England, Crathes Castle and Inveraray Castle in Scotland, Bodnant Garden in Wales, andMount Stewartin Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1100, 46, 'p19', 'Which TWO families started a civil war to decide who should be king of England in 1455?', 'checkbox', 'In 1455, a civil war was begun to decide who should be king of England. It was fought between the supporters of two families:the House of Lancaster and the House of York.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1101, 46, 'p20', 'Who was in charge of the British fleet at the Battle of Trafalgar?', 'radio', 'Admiral Nelsonwas in charge of the British fleet at Trafalgar and was killed in the battle.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1102, 46, 'p21', 'Which court deals with serious criminal offences in Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, serious offences are tried in front of a judge and a jury in aCrown Court. In Scotland, serious cases are heard in a Sheriff Court with either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1103, 46, 'p22', 'Which political party does the Speaker represent?', 'radio', 'The Speaker is neutral and does not represent a political party, even though he or she is an MP, represents a constituency and deals with the constituents’ problems like any other MP.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1104, 46, 'p23', 'When was the Scottish Parliament formed?', 'radio', 'The Scottish Parliament was formedin 1999.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1105, 47, 'p0', 'What characterised the Bronze Age?', 'radio', 'During the Bronze Age people lived in roundhouses and buried their dead in tombs called round barrows.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1106, 47, 'p1', 'What name is given to the elected members of the Scottish Parliament?', 'radio', 'Elected members of the Scottish Parliament are known as Members of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1107, 47, 'p2', 'Which game do people usually play at Halloween?', 'radio', 'During Halloween young people will often dress up in frightening costumes to play‘trick or treat’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1108, 47, 'p3', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries located in:', 'radio', 'The public can listen to debates in the Palace of Westminster from public galleries inboth the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1109, 47, 'p4', 'What is the most well-known gallery in Wales?', 'radio', 'In the UK, some of the most well-known galleries are The National Gallery, Tate Britain and Tate Modern in London,the National Museumin Cardiff, and the National Gallery of Scotland in Edinburgh.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1110, 47, 'p5', 'The Man Booker Prize for Fiction is awarded annually for the best fiction novel written by an author from:', 'radio', 'The Man Booker Prize for Fiction is awarded annually for the best fiction novel written by an author fromthe Commonwealth, Ireland or Zimbabwe. It has been awarded since 1968.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1111, 47, 'p6', 'Which of the following statements regarding Gaelic language is TRUE?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, Gaelic is spoken in some parts of the Highlands and Islands, and in Northern Ireland some people speak Irish Gaelic.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1112, 47, 'p7', 'Participation in community life is a fundamental principle of British life.', 'radio', 'The fundamental principles of British life include: participation in community life.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1113, 47, 'p8', 'How many British citizens left the country between 1853 and 1913?', 'radio', 'Between 1853 and 1913, as many as13 million British citizensleft the country.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1114, 47, 'p9', 'Where was the main Olympic site for the 2012 Games?', 'radio', 'The main Olympic site for the 2012 Games was inStratford, East London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1115, 47, 'p10', 'Who forms the shadow cabinet?', 'radio', 'The leader of the opposition also appoints senior opposition MPs to be ‘shadow ministers’. They form the shadow cabinet and their role is to challenge the government and put forward alternative policies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1116, 47, 'p11', 'Who directed the movie ‘Brief Encounter’ in 1945?', 'radio', 'Brief Encounter (1945) was directed byDavid Lean.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1117, 47, 'p12', 'Who was the leader of the English Republic?', 'radio', 'Oliver Cromwellwas the leader of the English republic.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1118, 47, 'p13', 'According to the 2011 Census, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Hindu?', 'radio', 'In the 2011 Census, 59% of people identified themselves as Christian. Much smaller proportions identified themselves as Muslim (4.8%),Hindu (1.5%), Sikh (0.8%), Jewish or Buddhist (both less than 0.5%).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1119, 47, 'p14', 'People in the UK have to pay tax on any earnings from (choose THREE options)?', 'checkbox', 'People in the UK have to pay tax on their income, which includes: wages from paid employment, profits from self-employment, taxable benefits, pensions and income from property, savings and dividends.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1120, 47, 'p15', 'How many devolved administrations are there in the UK?', 'radio', 'There arethreedevolved administrations in the UK, these include: the Welsh government, the Scottish Parliament and the Northern Ireland Assembly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1121, 47, 'p16', 'Who is responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly?', 'radio', 'Judges (who are together called‘the judiciary’) are responsible for interpreting the law and ensuring that trials are conducted fairly.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1122, 47, 'p17', 'How often do people who are 70 years old or over need to renew their driving licence?', 'radio', 'Drivers can use their driving licence until they are 70 years old. After that, the licence is valid forthree yearsat a time.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1123, 47, 'p18', 'Where was Margaret Thatcher born?', 'radio', 'Margaret Thatcher was the daughter of a grocer from Grantham inLincolnshire.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1124, 47, 'p19', 'Where are the Welsh government and the Senedd based?', 'radio', 'The Welsh government and Senedd are basedin Cardiff, the capital city of Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1125, 47, 'p20', 'Jenson Button is a famous:', 'radio', 'Jenson Button is a famousFormula 1 driver.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1126, 47, 'p21', 'Who introduced the Statute of Rhuddlan by which Wales was annexed to the Crown of England in 1284?', 'radio', 'In 1284King Edward I of Englandintroduced the Statute of Rhuddlan, which annexed Wales to the Crown of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1127, 47, 'p22', 'When was the Brexit referendum held?', 'radio', 'The Brexit referendum was held on23 June 2016.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1128, 47, 'p23', 'In the UK, alcohol cannot be sold to anyone under the age of:', 'radio', 'It is a criminal offence to sell alcohol to anyone who isunder 18or to buy alcohol for people who are under the age of 18. (There is one exception: people aged 16 or over can drink alcohol with a meal in a hotel or restaurant.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1129, 48, 'p0', 'Who was known as the Iron Duke?', 'radio', 'In 1815, the French Wars ended with the defeat of the Emperor Napoleon bythe Duke of Wellingtonat the Battle of Waterloo. Wellington was known as the Iron Duke and later became Prime Minister.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1130, 48, 'p1', 'Who appoints the members of the Cabinet?', 'radio', 'The Prime Minister (PM)is the leader of the political party in power. He or she appoints the members of the cabinet and has control over many important public appointments.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1131, 48, 'p2', 'Which of the following is NOT a British invention?', 'radio', 'The World Wide Web, the Turing machine and the hovercraft are British inventions. The mobile phone is not.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1132, 48, 'p3', 'When did Argentina invade the Falklands Islands?', 'radio', 'In1982, Argentina invaded the Falkland Islands, a British overseas territory in the South Atlantic.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1133, 48, 'p4', 'Which of the following statements is true?', 'radio', 'County Courts deal with a wide range ofcivil disputesincluding family matters, breaches of contract and divorce.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1134, 48, 'p5', 'When is Boxing Day?', 'radio', 'Boxing Day is on the26th of December, the day after Christmas Day and is a public holiday.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1135, 48, 'p6', 'According to 2011 Census, what percentage of the population identified themselves as Sikh?', 'radio', 'In the 2011 Census, 59% of people identified themselves as Christian. Much smaller proportions identified themselves as Muslim (4.8%), Hindu (1.5%),Sikh (0.8%), Jewish or Buddhist (both less than 0.5%).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1136, 48, 'p7', 'Which court usually deals with serious criminal cases in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, serious criminal cases are heard in aSheriff Courtwith either a sheriff or a sheriff with a jury. The most serious cases in Scotland, such as murder, are heard at a High Court with a judge and jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1137, 48, 'p8', 'Which of the following are British overseas territories?', 'checkbox', 'There are several British overseas territories in other parts of the world, such asSt Helena and the Falkland Islands. They are also linked to the UK but are not part of it.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1138, 48, 'p9', 'When did Alexander Fleming win the Nobel Prize in medicine for the discovery of the penicillin?', 'radio', 'Fleming won the Nobel Prize in Medicine in1945for the discovery of the penicillin.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1139, 48, 'p10', 'What is Sir Jackie Stewart famous for?', 'radio', 'Sir Jackie Stewart is a Scottish former racing driver who won the Formula 1 world championship three times.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1140, 48, 'p11', 'The decade of the 1960s was a period of significant social change, when there was growth in British fashion, cinema and popular music:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1141, 48, 'p12', 'When did Britain and France develop the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner known as ‘The Concorde’?', 'radio', 'The1960swas a time of technological progress, when Britain and France developed the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner, Concorde.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1142, 48, 'p13', 'When was the United Nations set up?', 'radio', 'The UN was set upafter the Second World Warand aims to prevent war and promote international peace and security.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1143, 48, 'p14', 'Where can you find copies of the ‘Hansard’?', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports called Hansard. Written reports can be foundin large libraries and at www.parliament.uk.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1144, 48, 'p15', 'Which court normally deals with cases of children aged 10 to 17 in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in aYouth Courtin front of up to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge. The most serious cases will go the Crown Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1145, 48, 'p16', 'How old do you need to be to be able to go into betting shops or gambling clubs?', 'radio', 'You have to be18to go into betting shops or gambling clubs.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1146, 48, 'p17', 'Which flag has a diagonal white cross on a blue ground?', 'radio', 'The cross of St Andrew, patron saint of Scotland, is a diagonal white cross on a blue ground.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1147, 48, 'p18', 'How long do Muslims fast for during Ramadan?', 'radio', 'Eid a-Fitr celebrates the end of Ramadan, when Muslims have fasted fora month.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1148, 48, 'p19', 'Which British actor has recently won an Oscar?', 'radio', 'Recent British actors to have won Oscars includeColin Firth, Sir Antony Hopkins, Dame Judi Dench, Kate Winslet and Tilda Swinton.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1149, 48, 'p20', 'Which was the first major railway built in Britain?', 'radio', 'The Great Western Railwaywas the first major railway built in Britain.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1150, 48, 'p21', 'In the 15th century, Henry Tudor, the leader of the House of Lancaster, became:', 'radio', 'In 1485, Henry Tudor, the leader of the House of Lancaster, becameKing Henry VIIafter defeating King Richard III of the House of York at the Battle of Bosworth Field.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1151, 48, 'p22', 'How many senior MPs are appointed by the Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The Prime Minister appointsabout 20 senior MPsto become ministers in charge of departments.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1152, 48, 'p23', 'Who won an Olympic gold medal in the pentathlon in 1972?', 'radio', 'Mary Peterswas a talented athlete who won an Olympic gold medal in the pentathlon in 1972.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
