(1536, 64, 'p23', 'How many years did Queen Victoria reign for?', 'radio', 'In 1837, Queen Victoria became queen of the UK at the age of 18. She reigned until 1901,almost 64 years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1537, 65, 'p0', 'The UK population is ethnically diverse and changing rapidly, especially in large cities such as London:', 'radio', 'The UK population is ethnically diverse and changing rapidly, especially in large cities such as London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1538, 65, 'p1', 'Which of the following is NOT a role of the King:', 'radio', 'The King receives foreign ambassadors and high commissioners, entertains visiting heads of state, and makes state visits overseas in support of diplomatic and relationships with other counties.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1539, 65, 'p2', 'The Speaker is a neutral MP and does not represent a political party:', 'radio', 'The Speaker is neutral and does not represent a political party, even though he or she is an MP, represents a constituency and deals with the constituents’ problems like any other MP.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1540, 65, 'p3', 'What is the height of the London Eye?', 'radio', 'The London Eye is situated on the southern bank of the River Thames and is a Ferris wheel that is43 feet (135 metres)tall.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1541, 65, 'p4', 'How can a person facing domestic violence find a safe place to stay (choose TWO options)?', 'checkbox', 'If you are facing domestic violence you can get help from the 24-hour National Domestic Violence Freephone Helpline on 0808 2000 247 at any time, or the police can help you find a safe place to stay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1542, 65, 'p5', 'What name is given to the celebration when people in Great Britain set off fireworks at home or in special displays on the 5th of November?', 'radio', 'Bonfire Night, 5 November, is an occasion when people in Great Britain set off fireworks at home or in special displays.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1543, 65, 'p6', 'When did the Vikings first visit Britain to raid coastal towns and take away goods and slaves?', 'radio', 'The Vikings came from Denmark and Norway. They first visited Britain inAD 789to raid coastal towns and take away goods and slaves.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1544, 65, 'p7', 'Who has control over policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security in Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'Policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security all remain undercentral UK government control. However, many other public services, such as education, are controlled by the devolved administrations.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1545, 65, 'p8', 'How many National Parks are there in England, Wales and Scotland?', 'radio', 'There are15 national parksin England, Wales and Scotland. They are areas of protected countryside that everyone can visit, and where people live, work and look after the landscape.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1546, 65, 'p9', 'Which services can be obtained from veterinary surgeons?', 'radio', 'Vaccinations and medical treatment for animals are available from veterinary surgeons (vets).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1547, 65, 'p10', 'The devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland cannot control policies and laws governing taxation and social security:', 'radio', 'Policy and laws governing defence, foreign affairs, immigration, taxation and social security all remain under central UK government control. However, many other public services, such as education, are controlled by the devolved administrations.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1548, 65, 'p11', 'The longer life expectancy in the UK has an effect on (choose TWO options):', 'checkbox', 'People in the UK are living longer than ever before. This is due to improved living standards and better health care. There are now a record number of people aged 85 and over. This has an impact onthe cost of pensions and health care.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1549, 65, 'p12', 'What percentage of the total British population is located in Scotland?', 'radio', 'The population is very unequally distributed over the four parts of the UK. England more or less consistently makes up 84% of the total population, Wales around 5%,Scotland just over 8%, and Northern Ireland less than 3%.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1550, 65, 'p13', 'When Cromwell died, his son, Richard, became Lord Protector in his place but was not able to control the army or the government:', 'radio', 'This istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1551, 65, 'p14', 'Which of the following academy awards are the equivalent of the Oscars in the UK?', 'radio', 'The annual British Academy Film Awards, hosted bythe British Academy of Film and Television Arts (BAFTA), are the British equivalent of the Oscars.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1552, 65, 'p15', 'Which political party was elected after the Second World War?', 'radio', 'The Labour Partywon the 1945 election. Clement Attlee was Prime Minister from 1945 to 1951 and led the Labour Party for 20 years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1553, 65, 'p16', 'Which British sportsman was captain of the English cricket team?', 'radio', 'Sir Ian Bothamcaptained the English cricket team and holds number of English Test cricket records, both for batting and for bowling.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1554, 65, 'p17', 'In which Japanese cities did the United States drop atomic bombs in August 1945?', 'radio', 'The war against Japan ended in August 1945 when the United States dropped its newly developed atom bombs on the Japanese cities ofHiroshima and Nagasaki.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1555, 65, 'p18', 'What is a bank holiday (choose TWO answers)?', 'checkbox', 'In the UK, there are public holidays each year called bank holidays, when banks and many other businesses are closed for the day.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1556, 65, 'p19', 'By 1200, the English ruled an area of Scotland known as the Pale, around Edinburgh:', 'radio', 'By 1200, the English ruled an area of Ireland known as the Pale,around Dublin.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1557, 65, 'p20', 'Which of the following countries does not take part in the Six Nations Championship?', 'radio', 'The most famous rugby union competition is the Six Nations Championship between England, Ireland, Scotland, Wales, France and Italy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1558, 65, 'p21', 'Who became Queen after Edward VI?', 'radio', 'Edward VI died at the age of 15 after ruling for just over six years, and his half-sisterMary became queen.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1559, 65, 'p22', 'Which of the following is NOT classified as a criminal offence in the UK?', 'radio', 'Cases of unfair dismissal or discrimination in the workplace are consideredcivil offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1560, 65, 'p23', 'The right to life and the right to liberty and security are some of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights:', 'radio', 'This istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1561, 66, 'p0', 'British values and principles are based on history and traditions and are protected by law, customs and expectations.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1562, 66, 'p1', 'When did the first Christian communities begin to appear in Britain?', 'radio', 'It wasduring the 3rd and 4th centuries ADthat the first Christian communities began to appear in Britain.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1563, 66, 'p2', 'Which of the following is NOT a devolved administration?', 'radio', 'There are three devolved administrations in the UK, this include: the Welsh government, the Scottish Parliament and the Northern Ireland Assembly', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1564, 66, 'p3', 'Who built a wall in the north of England to keep out the Picts (ancestors of the Scottish people)?', 'radio', 'Areas of what is now Scotland were never conquered by the Romans, and theEmperor Hadrianbuilt a wall in the north of England to keep out the Picts (ancestors of the Scottish people).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1565, 66, 'p4', 'Who looks after Edinburgh Castle?', 'radio', 'Edinburgh castle is a dominant feature of the skyline in Edinburgh, Scotland. It has a long history, dating back to the early Middle Ages. It is looked after byHistoric Environment Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1566, 66, 'p5', 'Each MP represents a parliamentary constituency, which is a small area of the country:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1567, 66, 'p6', 'Who were the pioneers of the IVF (in-vitro fertilisation) therapy?', 'radio', 'IVF (in-vitro fertilisation) therapy for the treatment of infertility was pioneered in Britain by physiologistSir Robert Edwards(1925-)andgynaecologistPatrick Steptoe(1913-88). The world’s first ‘test-tube baby’ was born in Oldham, Lancashire in 1978.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1568, 66, 'p7', 'Who led the establishment of the National Health System (NHS) in 1948?', 'radio', 'In 1948,Aneurin (Nye) Bevan, the Minister for Health, led the establishment of the National Health Service (NHS), which guaranteed a minimum standard of health care for all, free at the point of use.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1569, 66, 'p8', 'Which of the following countries were granted their independence in 1947 (choose THREE answers)?', 'checkbox', 'In 1947, independence was granted to nine countries, includingIndia, Pakistan and Ceylon (now Sri Lanka).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1570, 66, 'p9', 'In the UK, bank holidays of no religious significance are celebrated at the beginning of May, in late May or early June, and in August:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1571, 66, 'p10', 'Where can Admiral Nelson’s ship known as HMS Victory be visited?', 'radio', 'Admiral Nelson’s ship, HMS Victory, can be visited inPortsmouth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1572, 66, 'p11', 'Who were the Puritans?', 'radio', 'The Puritans werea group of Protestants who advocated strict and simple religious doctrine and worship. They did not agree with the king’s religious views and disliked his reforms of the Church of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1573, 66, 'p12', 'What TWO different types of rugby are practised in the UK?', 'checkbox', 'There are two different types of rugby, which have different rules:union and league.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1574, 66, 'p13', 'What do William Blake, John Keats and Lord Byron have in common?', 'radio', 'Poetry was very popular in the 19th century, with poets such as William Blake, John Keats, Lord Byron, Percy Shelley, Alfred Lord Tennyson, and Robert and Elizabeth Browning.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1575, 66, 'p14', 'The Laurence Olivier Awards take place annually at different venues in Liverpool:', 'radio', 'The Laurence Olivier Awards take place annually atdifferent venues in London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1576, 66, 'p15', 'An additional rented piece of land where people can grow fruit and vegetables is known as:', 'radio', 'In the UK, some people rent additional land called‘an allotment’, where they grow fruit and vegetables.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1577, 66, 'p16', 'What is the name of the battle where the Scottish led by Robert the Bruce defeated the English in 1314?', 'radio', 'In 1314 the Scottish, led by Robert the Bruce, defeated the English atthe Battle of Bannockburn.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1578, 66, 'p17', 'Who took the English throne after the death of Henry VIII?', 'radio', 'Henry VIII was succeeded by his sonEdward VI.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1579, 66, 'p18', 'Carrying a weapon is a criminal offence, unless it is for self-defence:', 'radio', 'It is a criminal offence to carry a weapon of any kind, even if it is for self-defence. This includes a gun, a knife or anything that is made or adapted to cause injury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1580, 66, 'p19', 'Prohibition of thought, conscience and religion is one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights:', 'radio', 'Freedom of thought, conscience and religion is one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1581, 66, 'p20', 'Which TWO pop music groups became popular in the 1960s?', 'checkbox', 'Two well-known pop music groups in the 1960s wereThe Beatles and The Rolling Stones.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1582, 66, 'p21', 'Which of the following words comes from the Viking language?', 'radio', 'Words such asGrimsby and Scunthorpecome from the Viking languages.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1583, 66, 'p22', 'Eid ul Adha is the day when Muslims thank Allah for giving them the strength to complete the fast:', 'radio', 'The day when Muslims thank Allah for giving them the strength to complete the fast is calledEid a-Fitr.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1584, 66, 'p23', 'Will a non-UK national living in the UK and looking for work, starting work or setting up as self-employed need a National Insurance number?', 'radio', 'A non-UK national living in the UK and looking for work, starting work or setting up as self-employed will need a National Insurance number. However, you can start work without one.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1585, 67, 'p0', 'What is the name of the highest mountain in Wales?', 'radio', 'Snowdonis the highest mountain in Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1586, 67, 'p1', 'Where did the Vikings come from?', 'radio', 'The Vikings came fromDenmark and Norway.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1587, 67, 'p2', 'Who led a Scottish army against Oliver Cromwell just after England had been declared a Republic?', 'radio', 'Charles IIwas crowned king of Scotland and led a Scottish army into England. Cromwell defeated this army in the Battles of Dunbar and Worcester.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1588, 67, 'p3', 'How many pence are there in a pound?', 'radio', 'There are100 pencein a pound.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1589, 67, 'p4', 'When are local elections for councillors held in most local authorities?', 'radio', 'For most local authorities, local elections for councillors are heldin Mayevery year.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1590, 67, 'p5', 'What sort of stories were collected by the Canterbury Tales written by Geoffrey Chaucer?', 'radio', 'In the years leading up to 1400, Geoffrey Chaucer wrote a series of poems in English about a group of people going to Canterbury on a pilgrimage. The people decided to tell each other stories on the journey, and the poemsdescribe the travellers and some of the stories they told. This collection poems is called The Canterbury Tales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1591, 67, 'p6', 'When did rugby originate?', 'radio', 'Rugby originated in Englandin the early 19th centuryand is very popular in the UK today.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1592, 67, 'p7', 'Which of the following lines does NOT form part of the citizenship pledge?', 'radio', 'Long live our noble King!is the second sentence of the National Anthem of the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1593, 67, 'p8', 'Which of the following is NOT protected by the laws of discrimination?', 'radio', 'UK laws ensure that people are not treated unfairly in any area of life or work because of their age, disability, sex, pregnancy and maternity, race, religion or belief, sexuality or marital status.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1594, 67, 'p9', 'Which Act abolished the old pocket and rotten boroughs and allowed more parliamentary seats to the towns and cities?', 'radio', 'The Reform Act of 1832had greatly increased the number of people with the right to vote. The act also abolished the old pocket and rotten boroughs and more parliamentary seats were given to the towns and cities.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1595, 67, 'p10', 'In the UK, if the jury finds a defendant guilty, the judge decides the penalty:', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1596, 67, 'p11', 'Which of the following countries is a member of the Commonwealth?', 'radio', 'Bangladeshis a member of the Commonwealth.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1597, 67, 'p12', 'During the Crusades, European Christians fought for the control of:', 'radio', 'European Christians fought for control ofthe Holy Land.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1598, 67, 'p13', 'The line ‘to be or not to be’ belongs to which of the following plays or poems written by William Shakespeare?', 'radio', '‘To be or not to be’ is a line from William Shakespeare’s playHamlet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1599, 67, 'p14', 'Charles I wanted the worship of the Church of England to include more ceremony and introduced a revised Prayer Book.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1600, 67, 'p15', 'Which of the following is NOT a principle included in the European Convention of Human Rights?', 'radio', 'Prohibition of immoral thoughtsis not one of the principles included in the European Convention of Human Rights.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1601, 67, 'p16', 'What was the name of the project through which the atomic bomb was developed?', 'radio', 'Scientists led by Ernest Rutherford, working at Manchester and then Cambridge University, were the first to ‘split the atom’ and took part inthe Manhattan Projectin the United States, which developed the atomic bomb.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1602, 67, 'p17', 'Who supported the Parliament during the Civil War that began in 1642?', 'radio', 'A civil war between the king and Parliament began in 1642. The country split into those who supported the king (the Cavaliers) and those who supported Parliament(the Roundheads).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1603, 67, 'p18', 'Which of the following poets wrote poems inspired by Scotland and the traditional stories and songs from the area on the borders of Scotland and England?', 'radio', 'Sir Walter Scott wrote poems inspired by Scotland and the traditional stories and songs from the area on the borders of Scotland and England', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1604, 67, 'p19', 'A system of government where the whole adult population gets a say is known as:', 'radio', 'Democracyis a system of government where the whole adult population gets a say. This might be by direct voting or by choosing representatives to make decisions on their behalf.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1605, 67, 'p20', 'Which of the following statements is correct?', 'radio', 'Arranged marriages refer to marriages whereboth parties agree to the marriage.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1606, 67, 'p21', 'The devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have the power to legislate on any issues that affect them:', 'radio', 'Devolved governments in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have the power to legislateon certain issues.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1607, 67, 'p22', 'What name is given to the members of the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'All of the electedMPsform the House of Commons.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1608, 67, 'p23', 'Which golf ‘Major’ tournament is held outside the United States?', 'radio', 'The open championshipis the only ‘Major’ tournament held outside the United States.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `test_id`, `question_id`, `question_text`, `question_type`, `explanation`, `created_at`) VALUES
(1609, 68, 'p0', 'As part of the citizenship ceremony, new citizens pledge their loyalty to the United Kingdom and to respect its rights and freedoms.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
