(1763, 74, 'p10', 'Which British landmark was built as part of the UK’s celebration of the new millenium?', 'radio', 'The London Eyewas originally built as part of the UK’s celebration of the new millennium and continues to be an important part of New Year celebrations.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1764, 74, 'p11', 'Where did slaves mainly come from during the slave trade?', 'radio', 'Slaves came primarily fromWest Africa.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1765, 74, 'p12', 'Who introduced ‘shampooing’ in Britain?', 'radio', 'Sake Dean Mahometand his wife also introduced ‘shampooing’, the Indian art of head massage, to Britain.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1766, 74, 'p13', 'To be able to vote in England, you have to register at your local council electoral registration office.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1767, 74, 'p14', 'Where can the Bayeux tapestry be seen?', 'radio', 'The Battle of Hastings is commemorated in a great piece of embroidery, known as the Bayeux tapestry, which can still be seenin Francetoday.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1768, 74, 'p15', 'It is an offence not to have an MOT certificate if your vehicle is more than two years old or without car insurance.', 'radio', 'It is an offence not to have an MOT certificate if your vehicle ismore than THREE years oldor without car insurance.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1769, 74, 'p16', 'What was the Spanish Armada?', 'radio', 'The Spanish Armada wasa large fleet of ships, which had been sent by Spain to conquer England and restore Catholicism.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1770, 74, 'p17', 'England was split into two groups during the English Civil War of 1642, which were known as:', 'radio', 'The English Civil war began in 1642. The country split into those who supported the king(the Cavaliers)and those who supported Parliament(the Roundheads).', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1771, 74, 'p18', 'What are the key roles of the governors and school boards? select THREE answers', 'checkbox', 'Governors and school boards have an important part to play in raising school standards. They have three key roles:setting the strategic direction of the school, ensuring accountability and monitoring and evaluating school performance.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1772, 74, 'p19', 'A popular way for people to stay in touch with friends, organise social events, and share photos, videos and opinions is through social networking websites such as:', 'radio', 'Social networking websites such asFacebook and Twitterare a popular way for people to stay in touch with friends, organise social events, and share photos, videos and opinions.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1773, 74, 'p20', 'Why is it important to recycle (select two answers)?', 'checkbox', 'It is important to recycle as much of your waste as you can. Using recycled materials to make new productsuses less energy and means that we do not need to extract more raw materials from the earth. It also means that less rubbish is created, so the amount being put into landfill is reduced.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1774, 74, 'p21', 'In Northern Ireland, a newly qualified driver must display an ____ plate for one year after passing the test.', 'radio', 'In Northern Ireland, a newly qualified driver must display an‘R’ plate(for restricted driver) for one year after passing the test.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1775, 74, 'p22', 'When is the birth of Jesus Christ celebrated?', 'radio', 'Christmas Day, 25 December, celebrates the birth of Jesus Christ.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1776, 74, 'p23', 'Prince William is also known as:', 'radio', 'Prince William is also known asthe Prince of Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1777, 75, 'p0', 'What are two responsibilities that you will have as a British citizen or permanent resident of the UK?', 'checkbox', 'If you wish to be a permanent resident or citizen of the UK, you should:look after yourself and your family, look after the area in which you live and the environment, respect and obey the law, respect the rights of others, including their right to their own opinions and treat others with fairness.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1778, 75, 'p1', 'Where is Big Ben located?', 'radio', 'Big Ben is the nickname for the great bell of the clockat the Houses of Parliament in London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1779, 75, 'p2', 'When were men and women given the right to vote at the age of 21?', 'radio', 'In1928, women were given the right to vote at the age of 21, the same as men.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1780, 75, 'p3', 'Where is the UK geographically located?', 'radio', 'The UK is located in thenorth west of Europe.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1781, 75, 'p4', 'Who is the patron Saint of Scotland?', 'radio', 'The patron Saint of Scotland isSt Andrew.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1782, 75, 'p5', 'Which two houses fought in the Wars of the Roses?', 'checkbox', 'The Wars of the Roses were fought between the supporters of two families:the House of Lancaster and the House of York.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1783, 75, 'p6', 'The Bill of Rights of 1689 confirmed the right to vote for all adult men.', 'radio', 'False. The Bill of Rights, 1689, confirmed the rights of Parliament and the limits of the king’s power.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1784, 75, 'p7', 'What is the Cenotaph?', 'radio', 'The Cenotaph isa war memorialand it is the site of the annual Remembrance Day service attended by the King, politicians and foreign ambassadors.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1785, 75, 'p8', 'Who was the first female Prime Minister of the UK?', 'radio', 'Margaret Thatcherwas the first woman Prime Minister of the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1786, 75, 'p9', 'Who chairs the debates at the House of Commons?', 'radio', 'Debates in the House of Commons are chaired bythe Speaker.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1787, 75, 'p10', 'Who was the captain of the English football team that won the World Cup in 1966?', 'radio', 'Bobby Moorecaptained the English football team that won the World Cup in 1966.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1788, 75, 'p11', 'When did the English defeat the Spanish Armada?', 'radio', 'In1588the English defeated the Spanish Armada.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1789, 75, 'p12', 'Anyone can make a complaint about the police by writing to the Chief Constable of the police force involved.', 'radio', 'This statement isTRUE.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1790, 75, 'p13', 'What is the minimum age required to serve on a jury?', 'radio', 'Anyone who is on the electoral register and is aged18to 70 can be asked to serve on a jury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1791, 75, 'p14', 'How is a jury selected?', 'radio', 'As well as getting the right to vote,people on the electoral register are randomly selectedto serve on a jury. Anyone who is on the electoral register and is aged 18 to 70 can be asked to do this.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1792, 75, 'p15', 'What is a bank holiday?', 'radio', 'There are public holidays each year called bank holidays,when banks and many other businesses are closed for the day.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1793, 75, 'p16', 'What will you be given to vote before a general election takes place?', 'radio', 'Before the election you will be sent apoll card.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1794, 75, 'p17', 'Which of the following statements is correct?', 'radio', 'Solicitors’ charges are usually based on how much time they spend of a case.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1795, 75, 'p18', 'By law, which TWO types of media have to give a balanced coverage of all political parties and equal time to rival viewpoints before an election?', 'checkbox', 'By law,radio and televisioncoverage of the political parties must be balanced and so equal time has to be given to rival viewpoints.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1796, 75, 'p19', 'Which of the following territories is a Crown dependency but is NOT part of the UK?', 'radio', 'The Channel Islandsis a British overseas territory linked to the UK, but it is not part of it.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1797, 75, 'p20', 'What did Sir Frank Whittle invent in the 1930s?', 'radio', 'Thejet enginewas developed in Britain in the 1930s bySir Frank Whittle.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1798, 75, 'p21', 'Who wrote ‘The Daffodils’?', 'radio', 'The British poetWilliam Wordsworthwrote ‘The Daffodils’.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1799, 75, 'p22', 'Who was given the title of Lord Protector?', 'radio', 'Oliver Cromwellwas given the title of Lord Protector and ruled until his death in 1658.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1800, 75, 'p23', 'What are the 40 days before Easter called?', 'radio', 'The 40 days before Easter are known asLent.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
