(1802, 76, 'p1', 'St Helena is a British overseas territory and it is part of the United Kingdom.', 'radio', 'British overseas territories, such as St Helena and the Falkland Islands are linked to the UK but arenot part of it.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1803, 76, 'p2', 'Several Church of England bishops sit in the House of Lords.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1804, 76, 'p3', 'When walking your dog in a public place, you must ensure:', 'radio', 'All dogs in public places must weara collar showing the name and address of the owner.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1805, 76, 'p4', 'Women over the age of 30 were given the right to vote as a result of their contribution towards the war effort. Which war was that?', 'radio', 'In 1918, women over the age of 30 were given voting rights and the right to stand for Parliament, partly in recognition of the contribution women made to the war effort during theFirst World War.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1806, 76, 'p5', 'When did Ireland become a republic?', 'radio', 'Ireland became a republic in1949.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1807, 76, 'p6', 'Where did the first farmers come from?', 'radio', 'The first farmers arrived in Britain 6,000 years ago. The ancestors of these first farmers probably came fromsouth-east Europe.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1808, 76, 'p7', 'Who was an important contributor to the ‘pop art’ movement of the 1960’s?', 'radio', 'David Hockneywas an important contributor to the ‘pop art’ movement of the 1960s and continues to be influential today.', '2025-08-02 08:38:44'),
(1809, 76, 'p8', 'Who became Prime Minister and was an inspirational leader to the British people during WWII?', 'radio', 'Winston Churchill.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1810, 76, 'p9', 'Who led the first invasion of Britain?', 'radio', 'Julius Caesarled a Roman invasion of Britain in 55 BC. This was unsuccessful and for nearly 100 years Britain remained separate from the Roman Empire. In AD 43 the Emperor Claudius led the Roman army in a new invasion. This time, there was resistance from some of the British tribes but the Romans were successful in occupying almost all of Britain.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1811, 76, 'p10', 'Under which king did the Anglo-Saxon kingdoms in England unite to defeat the Vikings?', 'radio', 'The Anglo-Saxon kingdoms in England united underKing Alfred the Great, who defeated the Vikings.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1812, 76, 'p11', 'When was the Magna Carta created?', 'radio', 'The Magna Carta was created in1215.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1813, 76, 'p12', 'Northern Ireland has its own banknotes, which are valid everywhere in the UK.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1814, 76, 'p13', 'Which of the following plays was written by William Shakespeare?', 'radio', 'William Shakespeare’s most famous plays includeA Midsummer Night’s dream.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1815, 76, 'p14', 'How many members does a jury have in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland a jury has12 members.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1816, 76, 'p15', 'Which two of the following religious communities celebrate Diwali?', 'checkbox', 'Diwali is celebrated byHindus and Sikhs.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1817, 76, 'p16', 'What is Good Friday?', 'radio', 'Good Fridaymarks the death of Jesus Christduring the Easter.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1818, 76, 'p17', 'St Patrick’s day is a public holiday in Northern Ireland.', 'radio', 'True. Only Scotland and Northern Ireland have their patron saint’s day as an official holiday (although in Scotland not all businesses and offices will close).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1819, 76, 'p18', 'Which was the last successful foreign invasion of England that took place in 1066?', 'radio', 'The Norman Conquestwas the last successful foreign invasion of England in 1066.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45');
