(1823, 76, 'p22', 'Which court deals with minor criminal cases in England, Wales and Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, most minor criminal cases are dealt with in aMagistrates’ Court. In Scotland, minor criminal offences go to a Justice of the Peace Court.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1824, 76, 'p23', 'What did the Scottish John Logie Baird develop?', 'radio', 'Thetelevisionwas developed by Scotsman John Logie Baird in the 1920s.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1825, 77, 'p0', 'Which of the following is a fundamental principle of British life?', 'radio', 'Individual libertyis the correct answer.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1826, 77, 'p1', 'Wales has its own established church.', 'radio', 'False. There is no established Church in Wales or Northern Ireland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1827, 77, 'p2', 'How is New Year’s Eve called in Scotland?', 'radio', 'In Scotland, the 31st of December (New Year’s Eve) is calledHogmanay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1828, 77, 'p3', 'Why did Henry VIII establish the church of England?', 'radio', 'To divorce his first wife, Henry needed the approval of the Pope. When the Pope refused, Henry established the church of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1829, 77, 'p4', 'What is the name of the long war that English kings fought with France in the middle ages?', 'radio', 'English kings fought a long war with France, calledthe Hundred Years War(even though it actually lasted 116 years).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1830, 77, 'p5', 'Who was supported by clansmen from the Scottish highlands and raised and army in 1745?', 'radio', 'In 1745 there was another attempt to put a Stuart king back on the throne in place of George I’s son, George II.Charles Edward Stuart (Bonnie Prince Charlie), the grandson of James II, landed in Scotland. He was supported by clansmen from the Scottish highlands and raised and army.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1831, 77, 'p6', 'If you think someone is trying to persuade you to join an extremist or terrorist activity, who should you contact?', 'radio', 'If you think someone is trying to persuade you to join an extremist or terrorist cause, you should notify yourlocal police force.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1832, 77, 'p7', 'It is compulsory for 16 and 17-year-olds to join the National Citizen Service programme.', 'radio', 'False. The National Citizen Service programme, which gives 16- and 17-year-olds the opportunity to enjoy outdoor activities, develop their skills and take part in a community project. Therefore,it is optional.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1833, 77, 'p8', 'What is the name of the tour guides that tell visitors stories about the Tower of London’s history?', 'radio', 'Tours are given at the Tower of London bythe Yeoman Warders, also known as Beefeaters, who tell visitors about the building’s history.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1834, 77, 'p9', 'Which two countries developed the Concorde, the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner?', 'checkbox', 'Britain and Francedeveloped the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner, Concorde.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
