(1847, 77, 'p22', 'Who was the first man in the world to run 1 mile in under 4 minutes?', 'radio', 'Sir Roger Bannisterwas the first man in the world to run a mile in under four minutes, in 1954.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1848, 77, 'p23', 'Which festival celebrates the end of Ramadan, when Muslims have fasted for a month?', 'radio', 'Eid al-Fitrcelebrates the end of Ramadan, when Muslims have fasted for a month.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1849, 78, 'p0', 'What was the last battle between Great Britain and France?', 'radio', 'In 1815, the French Wars ended with the defeat of the Emperor Napoleon by the Duke of Wellington atthe Battle of Waterloo.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1850, 78, 'p1', 'Which flower is associated with Wales?', 'radio', 'The flower associated with Wales is thedaffodil.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1851, 78, 'p2', 'During the reign of Charles II parts of London were destroyed, what was the cause of this destruction?', 'radio', 'During Charles II’s reign, a greatfiredestroyed much of the city, including many churches and St Paul’s Cathedral.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1852, 78, 'p3', 'How often are general elections held in the UK?', 'radio', 'MPs are elected at a General Election, which is held at leastevery five years.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1853, 78, 'p4', 'Scotland has its own banknotes, which are valid everywhere in the UK.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1854, 78, 'p5', 'What charity works to preserve important buildings, coastline and countryside in the UK?', 'radio', 'The National Trustis a charity that works to preserve important buildings, coastline and countryside in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1855, 78, 'p6', 'Great Britain refers only to England, Wales and Scotland.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1856, 78, 'p7', 'Who was the tribal leader who fought against the Romans?', 'radio', 'One of the tribal leaders who fought against the Romans wasBoudicca, the queen of the Iceni in what is now eastern England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1857, 78, 'p8', 'Who was voted the greatest Briton of all time in 2002?', 'radio', 'Winston Churchillremains a much-admired figure to this day, and in 2002 was voted the greatest Briton of all time by the public.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1858, 78, 'p9', 'Which two houses form the UK Parliament?', 'checkbox', 'The UK Parliament is formed of theHouse of Commons and the House of Lords.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1859, 78, 'p10', 'When did women get the right to vote at the same age as men?', 'radio', 'In1928, women were given the right to vote at the age of 21, the same as men.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1860, 78, 'p11', 'Who is the head of the Church of England?', 'radio', 'The monarchis the head of the Church of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
