(1862, 78, 'p13', 'What type of literature are the Canterbury Tales?', 'radio', 'Geoffrey Chaucer wrote a series of poems in English about a group of people going to Canterbury on a pilgrimage. Thiscollection of poemsis called The Canterbury Tales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1863, 78, 'p14', 'When is Christmas Day?', 'radio', 'Christmas Day is celebrated on the25th of December.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1864, 78, 'p15', 'Who supported King Charles I during the Civil War?', 'radio', 'During the civil war between the king and Parliament the country split intothose who supported the king (the Cavaliers)and those who supported Parliament (the Roundheads).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1865, 78, 'p16', 'What battle is commemorated in the Bayeux Tapestry?', 'radio', 'The Battle of Hastingsis commemorated in a great piece of embroidery, known as the Bayeux tapestry.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1866, 78, 'p17', 'Where was Anne Boleyn, the wife of Henry VIII, executed?', 'radio', 'Anne Boleyn was unpopular in the country and was accused of taking lovers. She was executedat the Tower of London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1867, 78, 'p18', 'Racial crime and smoking in public places are examples of:', 'radio', 'Racial crime and smoking in public places are examples ofcriminal offences.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1868, 78, 'p19', 'What type of character was played by Charlie Chaplin?', 'radio', 'Sir Charles (Charlie) Chaplin became famous in silent movies for histramp characterand was one of many British actors to make a career in Hollywood.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1869, 78, 'p20', 'You have to be at least 21 years old to stand as MP.', 'radio', 'This statement isfalse. Anyone aged 18 or over can stand for election as an MP but they are unlikely to win unless they have been nominated to represent one of the major political parties. These are the Conservative Party, the Labour Party, the Liberal Democrats, or one of the parties representing Scottish, Welsh or Northern Irish interests.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1870, 78, 'p21', 'Who developed the radar?', 'radio', 'Sir Robert Watson-Wattdeveloped the radar.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1871, 78, 'p22', 'Where is the official home of the Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The official home of the Prime Minister is10 Downing Street.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1872, 78, 'p23', 'By law, which TWO types of media have to give a balanced coverage of all political parties and equal time to rival viewpoints before an election?', 'checkbox', 'By law,radio and televisioncoverage of the political parties must be balanced and so equal time has to be given to rival viewpoints.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1873, 79, 'p0', 'When does Easter take place?', 'radio', 'Easter takes place inMarch or April.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
