(1989, 83, 'p20', 'What did ’the Butler Act’ introduce in 1944?', 'radio', 'Richard Austen Butler became a Conservative MP in 1923 and held several positions before becoming responsible for education in 1941. In this role, he oversaw the introduction of the Education Act 1944 (often called ‘The Butler Act’), which introducedfree secondary education in England and Wales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
