(1995, 84, 'p2', 'Boudicca, was a tribal leader who fought against which foreign invaders?', 'radio', 'One of the tribal leaders who fought againstthe Romanswas Boudicca, the queen of the Iceni.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1996, 84, 'p3', 'Which of the following poems is about a group of people going on a pilgrimage?', 'radio', 'Geoffrey Chaucer wrote a series of poems in English about a group of people going to Canterbury on a pilgrimage. The people decided to tell each other stories on the journey, and the poems describe the travellers and some of the stories they told. This collection of poems is calledThe Canterbury Tales.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1997, 84, 'p4', 'How are public holidays called?', 'radio', 'There are public holidays each year calledbank holidays, when banks and many other businesses are closed for the day.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1998, 84, 'p5', 'How did Charles II manage to escape to Europe after his defeat in the Civil War?', 'radio', 'Charles II escaped from Worcester, famouslyhiding in an oak treeon one occasion, and eventually fled to Europe.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(1999, 84, 'p6', 'Who defeated the Vikings?', 'radio', 'The Anglo-Saxon kingdoms in England united underKing Alfred the Great, who defeated the Vikings.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2000, 84, 'p7', 'Who was William Caxton?', 'radio', 'William Caxton wasthe first person in England to print books using a printing press.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2001, 84, 'p8', 'Where do Beefeaters serve as tour guides?', 'radio', 'Beefeaters serve as tour guides atthe Tower of London.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2002, 84, 'p9', 'During the rebellion of the clans in Scotland, Bonnie Prince Charlie was supported by clansmen from which Scottish region?', 'radio', 'Charles Edward Stuart (Bonnie Prince Charlie) was supported by clansmen fromthe Scottish Highlands.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2003, 84, 'p10', 'What religion did Elizabeth I follow?', 'radio', 'Elizabeth the I was aprotestant.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2004, 84, 'p11', 'Who became famous for his tramp character in silent movies?', 'radio', 'Charlie Chaplinbecame famous in silent movies for his tramp character.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2005, 84, 'p12', 'Which armed force was used in the Battle of Britain?', 'radio', 'The correct answer isthe Royal Air Force.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2006, 84, 'p13', 'In the UK, you have to be 21 years old to be able to vote in a general election.', 'radio', 'False. The present voting age of18was set in 1969 and (with a few exceptions) all UK-born and naturalised adult citizens have the right to vote.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2007, 84, 'p14', 'Which of the following poets was inspired by nature?', 'radio', 'British poets, includingWilliam Wordsworth, were inspired by nature.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2008, 84, 'p15', 'Against which country did Britain fight at the Battle of Waterloo?', 'radio', 'In 1815, theFrenchWars ended with the defeat of the Emperor Napoleon by the Duke of Wellington at the Battle of Waterloo.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2009, 84, 'p16', 'Who was William Wilberforce?', 'radio', 'William Wilberforce, an evangelical Christian and a member of Parliament, also played an important part in changing the law. Along with other abolitionists (people who supported the abolition of slavery), he succeeded in turning public opinion against the slave trade.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2010, 84, 'p17', 'Who is the spiritual leader of the Church of England?', 'radio', 'The spiritual leader of the Church of England isthe Archbishop of Canterbury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2011, 84, 'p18', 'James I was King of which country before becoming King of England?', 'radio', 'When Elizabeth I died, her cousinJames VI of Scotland became King James I of England, Wales and Irelandand Scotland remained a separate country.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2012, 84, 'p19', 'Which of the following statements is correct?', 'radio', 'Most shops in the UK are open seven days a week, although trading hours on Sundays and public holidays are generally reduced.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2013, 84, 'p20', 'Which country sent a fleet of ships to England in 1588?', 'radio', 'Elizabeth became one of the most popular monarchs in English history, particularly after 1588, when the English defeated the Spanish Armada (a large fleet of ships), which had been sent bySpainto conquer England and restore Catholicism.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2014, 84, 'p21', 'Where is the National Horseracing Museum located?', 'radio', 'There is a National Horseracing Museum inNewmarket, Suffolk.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2015, 84, 'p22', 'Which of the following castles is located in Scotland?', 'radio', 'Crathes Castleis located in Scotland.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2016, 84, 'p23', 'Who was a famous Art Deco ceramic designer?', 'radio', 'Britain has produced many great designers, from Thomas Chippendale (who designed furniture in the 18th century) toClarice Cliff(who designed Art Deco ceramics) to Sir Terence Conran (a 20th-century interior designer).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2017, 85, 'p0', 'When is St Patrick’s day celebrated?', 'radio', 'St Patrick’s day, patron of Northern Ireland is celebrated on the17th of March.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2018, 85, 'p1', 'How are the members of the Northern Ireland Parliament elected?', 'radio', 'The Northern Ireland Assembly has 90 elected members, known as MLAs (members of the Legislative Assembly). They are electedwith a form of proportional representation.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2019, 85, 'p2', 'Who was the first British Prime Minister?', 'radio', 'The most important minister in Parliament became known as the Prime Minister. The first man to be called this wasSir Robert Walpole, who was Prime Minister from 1721 to 1742.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2020, 85, 'p3', 'Which of the following actresses has not won an Oscar?', 'radio', 'British actors to have won Oscars include Colin Firth, Sir Antony Hopkins, Dame Judi Dench, Kate Winslet and Tilda Swinton.Emily Watson has not won an Oscar yet.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2021, 85, 'p4', 'During the Enlightenment, Adam Smith developed ideas about:', 'radio', 'During ’the Enlightenment’ Adam Smith developed ideas abouteconomicswhich are still referred to today.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2022, 85, 'p5', 'Who died at the Battle of Trafalgar?', 'radio', 'Admiral Nelsonwas in charge of the British fleet at Trafalgar and was killed in the battle.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2023, 85, 'p6', 'When is Hogmanay celebrated?', 'radio', 'In Scotland,the 31st of Decemberis called Hogmanay.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2024, 85, 'p7', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports known as:', 'radio', 'Proceedings in Parliament are broadcast on television and published in official reports calledHansard.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2025, 85, 'p8', 'Which of the following is a rugby competition?', 'radio', 'The most famous rugby union competition isthe Six Nations Championshipbetween England, Ireland, Scotland, Wales, France and Italy.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2026, 85, 'p9', 'Who appoints life peers in the House of Lords?', 'radio', 'Life peers are appointed bythe monarchon the advice of the Prime Minister.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2027, 85, 'p10', 'Who mapped the coast of Australia?', 'radio', 'Captain James Cookmapped the coast of Australia and a few colonies were established there.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2028, 85, 'p11', 'What was the first war to be extensively covered by the media?', 'radio', 'The Crimean Warwas the first war to be extensively covered by the media through news stories and photographs.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2029, 85, 'p12', 'Which of the following monuments is located in Wiltshire?', 'radio', 'Stonehengestands in what is now the English county of Wiltshire.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2030, 85, 'p13', 'Who was the first Archbishop of Canterbury?', 'radio', 'St Augustineled missionaries from Rome, who spread Christianity in the south. St Augustine became the first Archbishop of Canterbury.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2031, 85, 'p14', 'How old do you have to be to go into betting shops or gambling clubs?', 'radio', 'You have to be18to go into betting shops or gambling clubs.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2032, 85, 'p15', 'The system of government in the UK is a parliamentary democracy.', 'radio', 'This statement istrue.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2033, 85, 'p16', 'What is the traditional food of Northern Ireland?', 'radio', 'Ulster fryis the correct answer.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2034, 85, 'p17', 'Who was elected as British Prime Minister in 1945?', 'radio', 'In 1945 the British people elected a Labour government. The new Prime Minister wasClement Attlee.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2035, 85, 'p18', 'How many times has the UK hosted the Olympic games?', 'radio', 'The UK has hosted the Olympic games onthreeoccasions: 1908, 1948 and 2012.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2036, 85, 'p19', 'Why were canals built during the Industrial Revolution?', 'radio', 'Canals were builtto link the factories to towns and cities and to the ports, particularly in the new industrial areas in the middle and north of England.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2037, 85, 'p20', 'Are civil servants appointed by the government?', 'radio', 'Civil servantsare accountable to ministers. They are chosen on merit and are politically neutral – theyare not political appointees.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2038, 85, 'p21', 'Which of the following countries helped Britain to develop the Concorde?', 'radio', 'Britain andFrancedeveloped the world’s only supersonic commercial airliner, Concorde.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `test_id`, `question_id`, `question_text`, `question_type`, `explanation`, `created_at`) VALUES
(2039, 85, 'p22', 'Which invention led to the development of Britain during the Industrial Revolution?', 'radio', 'The Industrial Revolution was the rapid development of industry in Britain in the 18th and 19th centuries. Britain was the first country to industrialise on a large scale. It happened because of the development of machinery and the use ofsteam power.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2040, 85, 'p23', 'Who was the tribal leader who fought against the Romans?', 'radio', 'One of the tribal leaders who fought against the Romans wasBoudicca.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2041, 86, 'p0', 'Which two languages were used across England during the Middle Ages?', 'checkbox', 'The Middle Ages saw the development of a national culture and identity. After the Norman Conquest, the king and his noblemen had spokenNorman Frenchand the peasants had continued to speakAnglo-Saxon.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2042, 86, 'p1', 'In 1776, which British colonies declared their independence because they demanded that there should be ‘no taxation without representation‘.', 'radio', 'In 1776, 13North Americancolonies declared their independence, stating that people had a right to establish their own governments.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2043, 86, 'p2', 'When was England ruled by a republic and not by a monarch?', 'radio', 'When Charles I was executed, England declared itself a republic, called the Commonwealth. It no longer had a monarch.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2044, 86, 'p3', 'Which film produced in the UK was one of the most commercially successful films of all time and one of the highest-grossing film franchises?', 'radio', 'Some of the most commercially successful films of all time, including the two highest-grossing film franchises (Harry Potterand James Bond), have been produced in the UK.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2045, 86, 'p4', 'When did the first farmers come to Britain?', 'radio', 'The first farmers arrived in Britain6,000 years ago.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2046, 86, 'p5', 'When did the First World War end?', 'radio', 'The First World War endedat 11.00 am on 11th November 1918with victory for Britain and its allies.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2047, 86, 'p6', 'Can court orders be obtained to protect a person from being forced into a marriage?', 'radio', 'True. Court orders can be obtained to protect a person from being forced into a marriage, or to protect a person in a forced marriage.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2048, 86, 'p7', 'What medal did Mary Peters win in the 1972 Olympics?', 'radio', 'Born in Manchester, Mary Peters moved to Northern Ireland as a child. She was a talented athlete who wonan Olympic gold medalin the pentathlon in 1972.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2049, 86, 'p8', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland Youth Court cases are normally heard by (choose TWO answers)?', 'checkbox', 'In England, Wales and Northern Ireland, if an accused person is aged 10 to 17, the case is normally heard in a Youth Court in front ofup to three specially trained magistrates or a District Judge.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2050, 86, 'p9', 'What was invented by Alan Turing in the 1930s?', 'radio', 'ATuring machineis a theoretical mathematical device invented by Alan Turing (1912-54), a British mathematician, in the 1930s.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2051, 86, 'p10', 'Which of the following tells us about how people lived in England just after the Norman Conquest?', 'radio', 'William sent people all over England to draw up lists of all the towns and villages. The people who lived there, who owned the land and what animals they owned were also listed. This was calledthe Domesday Book. It still exists today and gives a picture of society in England just after the Norman Conquest.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2052, 86, 'p11', 'Who led a team of scientists to ‘split the atom‘ for the first time?', 'radio', 'Scientists led byErnest Rutherford, working at Manchester and then Cambridge University, were the first to ‘split the atom‘ and took part in the Manhattan Project in the United States, which developed the atomic bomb.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2053, 86, 'p12', 'What song is sung by people in the UK and other countries when they are celebrating the New Year?', 'radio', 'The song Auld Lang Syne, which is sung by people in the UK and other countries when they are celebrating the New Year (or Hogmanay as it is called in Scotland).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2054, 86, 'p13', 'Who fought in the English Civil war of 1642?', 'radio', 'The Civil war between the king and Parliament began in 1642. The country split into those who supported the king (the Cavaliers) and those who supported Parliament (the Roundheads).', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2055, 86, 'p14', 'Which two of these forts were part of Hadrian‘s wall?', 'checkbox', 'Parts of Hadrian‘s Wall, include the forts ofHousesteads and Vindolanda.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2056, 86, 'p15', 'What was the religion of the Puritans?', 'radio', 'The Puritans were a group ofProtestantswho advocated strict and simple religious doctrine and worship.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2057, 86, 'p16', 'What is the name of Irish people who favoured complete independence from the UK in the 19th century?', 'radio', 'The Irish Nationalist movement had grown strongly through the 19th century. Some, such asthe Fenians, favoured complete independence.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2058, 86, 'p17', 'Which two British pop music groups were famous during the Swinging Sixties?', 'checkbox', 'The decade of the 1960s was a period of significant social change. It was known as the ‘swinging sixties’. There was growth in British fashion, cinema and popular music. Two well-known pop music groups at the time wereThe BeatlesandThe Rolling Stones.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2059, 86, 'p18', 'What is the minimum age required to drive a motorcycle?', 'radio', 'In the UK, you must be at least17years to drive a car or motorcycle and you must have a driving licence to drive on public roads.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2060, 86, 'p19', 'The members of the House of Lords, known as peers, are elected by the people.', 'radio', 'False. The members of the House of Lords, known as peers,are not elected by the people.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2061, 86, 'p20', 'When did the Emancipation Act abolish slavery throughout the British Empire?', 'radio', 'In1833the Emancipation Act abolished slavery throughout the British Empire.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2062, 86, 'p21', 'Who is responsible for crime, policing and immigration?', 'radio', 'The Home Secretaryis responsible for crime, policing and immigration.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2063, 86, 'p22', 'What kind of genre was the film Wallace and Gromit created by Nick Park?', 'radio', 'Nick Park won four Oscars for hisanimated films, including three for films featuring Wallace and Gromit.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45'),
(2064, 86, 'p23', 'Anyone who is violent towards their partner – whether they are a man or a woman, married or living together – can be prosecuted.', 'radio', 'True. Anyone who is violent towards their partner – whether they are a man or a woman, married or living together – can be prosecuted.', '2025-08-02 08:38:45');
